so very excited to find this gem!

text:
emmeline pankhurst is the woman of the day;
although she wasn’t perfect, she demanded equality for woman as the leader of the suffragette movement. her efforts led to the vote being granted to some women (those over the age of 30 who owned property or were married to a man who owned property) in 1918.
underestimate the power of a fearless woman at your peril – suffragettes threw themselves under horses, chained themselves to railings and starved themselves for the right to vote.

text:
do not come up to me and say 'there is no evidence, no witness. how can you believe her?' because i will have you know that i believe her.
i don't care if she has been my lifelong enemy, if she says she has been assaulted, i believe her, not a second thought.
i don't care if i don't know her, if we've never talked, if she tells me she was harassed, i feel it my duty that i take her word for it. this is not just me, this is the way to do it. and if you think you are exempted from this because you haven't been personally attacked, then look again, there's something that needs fixing. 🙌🏻 #feminism #feminist  #society #comparing #men #women #betterpeople #rights #equality #life #understand #loveyourself #spreadlove #boys #girls #girlpower #feministquotes #beyourself #transpeople #equity #worldpeace #bekind #womenrights #menrights #birthcontrol #politics #messedup #society #strangeworld #metoo #metoomovement

text:
a live durational performance by colombian- born artist, nathalie alfonso, entitled “ underscore,” an incessant rhythm of washing away her own work that visualizes invisible labor along the facade of fair market.

last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

photo: diana larrea / @parcialmentenublada

#nathaliealfonso #underscore #genderequality #brickellcitycentre #fairmarket #fairatbcc #wearehere #spinelloprojects

text:
" i have been finding it really hard to put my thoughts into words. it’s often confusing and confronting and difficult to address the abuse or the sexism you have faced, but haven’t had the courage to publicly address for so long.

like most other victims/survivors, i blamed myself for a long time.

the men i want to write about today are sajid khan, zain durrani, and vikas bahl.

before i tell you what happened with me, i want people to remember that #metoo isn’t about hollywood or bollywood — it’s about you being able to speak up about people that have abused you, it’s about sexism, it’s about you having a voice and not being scared to address the people that think it’s okay to misuse their power over you. it’s about not blaming yourself.

industries like these help because they are in the limelight. the media doesn’t always want to cover it when it’s your father or your uncle, and that’s the harsh truth. but the fact that famous people are being named, is supposed to give you the courage to speak up. for years, girls have been trying to speak up — often, they’re silenced. but today this movement is supposed to help you come out with your stories. whether its a family member or a friend or a co worker or an ex lover or a current partner or just a one off date — tell someone you trust. speak about the abuse. don’t let all the attention that’s been given to the film industries take away from your story. your story may not make it in the news, but people, all over this country are only trying to cover the stories of these famous people to give you the courage to speak. i, today, am talking about my story to remind you, that so can you.

because i didn’t know where to begin, and who to begin with, i’m going to begin right at the start and hope you stay till the end. "
- @redheadwayfarer

warning: this post is political in nature.  you’re welcome to ignore it, but good luck living without a soul... in 1991, anita hill came forward with her assault allegations against justice clarence thomas. her accusations were met with the same dismissive treatment as was recently endured by dr. christine blasey ford. after the hearings, anita hill began receiving handwritten letters of support and gratitude for having stood up and told her story. 
in an article for time magazine that came out in 2011, anita hill explained how those letters comforted her and motivated her to keep fighting the good fight - and not just against sexual harassment but against gender, racial, class and ethnic inequality. 
dr. christine blasey ford deserves the same messages of support for having stood up so publicly against her abuser. 
so here is what i’d like to do - if you send me a dm with your address, i will send you, free of charge, a small package which will include a stamped envelope addressed to dr. ford and a card for you to write her a message. assholes need not apply. ✖️

text:
all of us have our struggles of everyday. some are major, some are minor. but we live through them. most of the people around us aren’t even aware about them, nor are we aware about the other people around. but still we all do. this #mentalhealth day i would like to recognise it. not just mine, not just yours our struggles our (minor/major) victories of every day life. 💐

feel free to share your thoughts/stories with me or with anyone around. 
do share. you know it feels nice to be heard. don’t you?
_____________________________

text:
reformist female lawmakers in iran have called on president rouhani to follow through on an unfulfilled campaign promise and choose a woman to fill his government's next ministerial vacancy.⠀
⠀
“we members of the women’s faction call upon mr. rouhani to introduce at least one female candidate for a ministerial post,” said the parliamentary faction’s leader, tehran representative farideh oladghobad, in an interview with etemad newspaper on october 11. “based on articles 20 and 21 of the constitution, women and men enjoy equal social, cultural and economic rights.” ⠀
⠀

text:
przemoc w kinie. o warunkach pracy w branży filmowej

data: 18 października, czwartek, godz. 17:00
goście: agnieszka holland, greta gober, natalia grzegorzek
prowadzenie: michał pabiś-orzeszyna

porozmawiamy o warunkach pracy w różnych sektorach branży filmowej w polsce. poruszymy temat seksizmu, ageizmu, rasizmu czy klasizmu. szczególną uwagę poświęcimy relacjom władzy, wykluczeniom i niesprawiedliwości oraz nieformalnym hierarchiom w kinematografii. goście będą dyskutować o zmowach milczenia w temacie tego, co dzieje się na planach filmowych, o akcji #metoo. co ważne, nie skupimy się tylko na akcji “kobiety filmu 50/50 w 2020”, porozmawiamy o szklanym suficie nie tylko ze względu na płeć. jaką rolę pełnią kierownicy/czki produkcji, drugi reżyser/ka, na ile może pozwolić sobie dźwiękowiec/wczyni, a na ile aktor/ka na planie. z kilku perspektyw o tym aktualnym temacie opowiedzą: światowej sławy reżyserka agnieszka holland, producentka filmów “kamper” i “córka trenera” natalia grzegorzek oraz badaczka mediów i członkini międzynarodowego sojuszu równości w mediach greta gober.
@szkolafilmowawlodzi

#kameraakcja #jestemkrytykiem #łódź #kochamkino #kochamlodz #wszyscyjestesmykrytykami #fka #przemocwkinie #gender #genderbalans
name: Festiwal Kamera Akcja

text:
for those who are still unaware about the allegations faced by co founder of @ttt_official.
we are sharing this post to support shrutee choudhary and others who came out bravely. below is the full post by shrutee. .
dear chintan (@thethirdalphabet),
. 
you came to me at a point in my life when i was already too broken, but you had a soft spot for broken souls, didn’t you tell me? that first night, when you’d ‘discovered’ my ‘writing’ on instagram, we spoke for hours. i thought we connected, and i’d been longing for a soulful connection ever since my heart had still been intact. so i opened up to you, slowly, gradually over many spontaneous meetings, and extremely poetic conversations. i wouldn’t lie when i say the first few moments didn’t feel magical. when you shared your story with me, and as did i. the silence was still comforting and there was an innocence to our bond – we used to hold hands for so long. maybe, i idealised you into a someone who was completely different from the real version. or maybe for that brief moment, you were really being genuine. i don’t know. it’s tough to say now. the memory of our first kiss is vague. but i remember the feeling, and don’t you claim to be all about that too? you said you hadn’t felt so strongly for someone in a long time and how could i not believe you – you seemed like a dream come true of sorts. you were that one person i unraveled my wounded soul to, you were a place of trust.

and then we had scotland. do you remember what you’d told me before we left? that you wouldn’t even touch me if i was uncomfortable, that you respect me too much and you care. cut to the first night in that bedroom, you were already on top of me. i said no. you apologised and admitted to the fact that it’s hard to control the urges around me. again, brownie points for making me feel special. then you tried again, i said no, again. it wounded your ego and you faced away from me in the far corner of the bed, making me feel like shit, stained in guilt, extremely uncomfortable.
.
continued in comments.
. 
allegations by shrutee choudhury (@shruteechoudhary)
.
#theprojectquote #ttt #terriblytinytales #metoomovement #metoo
name: The Project Quote

and then we had scotland. do you remember what you’d told me before we left? that you wouldn’t even touch me if i was uncomfortable, that you respect me too much and you care. cut to the first night in that bedroom, you were already on top of me. i said no. you apologised and admitted to the fact that it’s hard to control the urges around me. again, brownie points for making me feel special. then you tried again, i said no, again. it wounded your ego and you faced away from me in the far corner of the bed, making me feel like shit, stained in guilt, extremely uncomfortable.
.
continued in comments.
. 
allegations by shrutee choudhury (@shruteechoudhary)
.

text:
ett år efter #metoo läser jag darling river. sara stridsberg har vladimir nobokovs lolita som utgångspunkt för sin bok. i lolita finns tonårsdottern dolores och stridsbergs darling river har underrubriken 'doloresvariationer.' det är just vad vi får i form av några kvinnor och ett djur. de är bortom räddning, livegna och i männens våld.

en fullständig vrickad och sinnessjuk forskare studerar en apa som tvingas rita och genomgå forskarens "undersökningar". lo kallar sina älskare för bröder (för att undvika känslan av att vara offer) och tar dem till darling river medan pappan väntar i jaguaren.
en moder försöker fly från sig själv genom att resa runt i världen, men misslyckas.
delores, "en dagslända som flyger mot den sjunkande solen, en meningslös insekt som blir ihjälslagen redan på morgonen", föder ett dödfött barn och dör i barnsäng.

vid några tillfällen dyker en kort passage med rubriken 'encyklopedi' upp, där författaren lägger ut sina ord kring det hon så intensivt har skildrat. som en extra förklaring till läsaren. med tyngd.

jag ser färger ner jag färdas mellan raderna. svart, lila och bärnstensgult. språket - ett pärlband av återkommande symboler. 
fjärilar. koboltfjärilar med svedda vingar, nattsvarta fjärilar, fjärilsformad tumör.
speglar. 'att fastna i en spegel är att fastna i en dröm', skriver stridsberg, och sedan utbildar hon mig i spegelparadoxen.
ögon. här finns ögon som grumlas, som täcks med en vit hinna och till sist finns inget synfält kvar. blind.

stridsberg blåser liv i tingen. sjön spottar ur sig ett lik, cigarettglöden sicksackar i mörker och "träden står avklädda som om de aldrig mer ska orka bära blad igen." ja, hennes språk är poetiskt när hon beskriver det ohyggliga! 
darling river, en mörk historia där bränderna aldrig upphör, och när du läst är du brännmärkt för livet. så kändes det igår kväll när jag läste de sista raderna. men i morse, på väg till arbetet, påminde p1 mig om att vi lever i förändringarnas tid. "jag var inskriven i tiden som en fjäril i en bärnsten, fastnaglad, förutbestämd", säger lo i darling river. 
jag säger: vi ristar in #metoo i en bärnsten och flyger högt på stadiga vingar!

text:
🔔 gender-based violence installation.

this installation focused on those who has ever been violated. we made a huge muted bell out of paper plates.

a bell is usually used to call a community together or to warn them from danger.

this bell is muted.

the muted bell represents the voices that has been silenced and unacknowledged with regards to gender based violence.

the uct community was urged to write their story of how they were violated whether it was physical, emotional of vocal (such as cat calling). this artwork was a great success with stories written all over which is very sad an unfortunate.

thank you for everyone respecting the cause and for those participating.

#genderbasedviolence #metoo #menaretrash #installationart #conceptart #conceptualart #art #change

text:
i believe most of us can to relate to the following story submission in one way or another, unfortunately. the writer has chosen to remain anonymous.

i was about 19 when one day i boarded a public bus in my hometown. the bus was practically empty, but this man came and sat next to me. the bus hadn't still started to move when he started playing something on his mobile phone, and it seemed like be was trying to show it to me. i saw from the corner of my eye that it was a porn clip. i froze for a bit and didn't know how to react. but then i found my voice and told him to sit somewhere else. he just got off the bus. so i guess that's all he came on the bus for. there have been other times when my breasts and waist have been touched in crowded buses. unfortunately that time i just felt that this is normal because every girl has to put up with this. i have undergone harassment in my home as well. my maths tutor used to touch my arm from time to time while teaching, my art teacher used to hug me on the pretext of applauding me. i could tell something was wrong, i didn't feel comfortable. but as i always thought, this is how people show affection. now that i hear all these stories of different people, i am glad that at least one of my parents always stayed home when i had home tutors coming over. they were concerned about my safety.

text: went to massage therapy today she asked how i was i sobbed i don’t want a body anymore / today was therapy day i told my psychotherapist the last buried secret / there have been multiple abuses perpetrated on this body and after 20 yrs of therapy i have told about all but one and i told i told two ppl this week about the last secret that was too too too too too shameful (only it’s really a portmanteau / egg sac of sub-secrets) // today patriarchy i am not coming for you i am coming for *me* / the me that i was / i am going to lift her up and hold her so close // this shit is probably gonna get worse before it gets better // my hands are shaking as i type this but today was a triumph don’t you dare read it any other way // #ptsd #metoo #nomoresecrets

text:
🔔 gender-based violence installation.

this installation focused on those who has ever been violated. we made a huge muted bell out of paper plates.

a bell is usually used to call a community together or to warn them from danger.

this bell is muted.

the muted bell represents the voices that has been silenced and unacknowledged with regards to gender based violence.

the uct community was urged to write their story of how they were violated whether it was physical, emotional of vocal (such as cat calling). this artwork was a great success with stories written all over which is very sad an unfortunate.

thank you for everyone respecting the cause and for those participating.

#genderbasedviolence #metoo #menaretrash #installationart #conceptart #conceptualart #art #change

text:
it's unfortunate that a picture of 'vastra harana' by  lord krishna is being cicrculated in social media and the gopis have been tagged with #metoo. lord krishna is being protrayed as a molester. judging an incident which took place thousand of years ago without having concrete knowledge about the society of that time is nothing but foolishness. this futile attempt becomes a laughable stock when people with limited knowledge judge lord krishna who stands beyond any words, expressions and intellects. again these pseudo-intellectuals are spinning the facts to  justify their malicious intention of maligning and diluting hinduism by raising suspicion among the followers. the act of vastra harana by lord krishna was a metaphorical one, which distinguishes between reality and illusions. the worldly possessions like clothes and ornaments can be compared with illusions. again it can be taken as a childish prank of bal-gopal as he was just 6/7 years old then. our feminists have used the picture of a young krishna instead of the child-krishna. the depiction of vastra harana doesn't have any kind of explicit or implicit sexual connotations. they have trickily overlooked this aspect of the scriptural description. most importantly all the gopis were in immensely love with lord krishna. it was clearly evident when with their mothers' permission, they performed katyani vrata to get lord krishna as their husband. finally these feminists need to remember that it's the sole prerogative of a lady to decide whether an incident comes under the #metoo moment or not ! if gopis had no problems, then you are a nobody to interfere in their personal affairs. that's probably a real form women empowerment.
#lordkrishna #hinduism #metoo #india #iskcon

text:
सौ चूहे खाकर बिल्ली हज को चली- कुछ जानने लायक बातें तनु श्री दत्ता के बारे में कुछ दिनों से बॉलीवुड की एक अदाकारा तनु श्री दत्ता का नाम #metoo  campaign के साथ पूरे देश की सुर्खियों में चल रहा है, तनु श्री नाम की यह महिला ने बॉलीवुड में एक अश्लील गाने (adult) से अपने फिल्मी कैरियर की शुरुआत की जिसका नाम है "आशिक बनाया..." ऐसा गाना जो कोई भी सभ्य व्यक्ति अपने परिवार के साथ बैठकर नहीं देख सकेगा कुछ 10 साल पहले अपनी शूटिंग के दौरान हुई घटना के बाद इन्हें किसी भी फिल्म में काम मिलना बंद होने की वजह से अवसादग्रस्त होकर इन्होंने नशे का सहारा लिया जो कि बॉलीवुड की दुनिया में सामान्य बात है, फिर इन्होने स्ट्रेस से मुक्त होने के लिए अध्यात्म का सहारा लेना उचित समझा, कुछ बोद्ध धर्म से प्रभावित हुई वहां भी इनकी आत्मा को अध्यात्मिक संतुष्टि नहीं मिली, फिर इन्होने ईसाई धर्म में अध्यात्म खोजा और धर्म बदल लिया विदेश जाकर नागरिकता भी बदली पिछले 10 साल की अध्यात्म यात्रा के पश्चात मन के विकारों में कमी तो हुई नहीं विकारों ने षणयंत्र को जन्म दिया और वापस भारत में छुट्टी मनाने के बहाने से आई और विदेश से #metoo... नाम का हथियार साथ में लाती है, कुछ ही दिनों में वर्षों पुरानी तनु श्री जिसे भारतीय लगभग भूल से गए थे वो प्रसिध्द हो जाती है, और आरोप लगाती है इस देश के लोगों को बुरा भला कहती है सभी को कटघरे में रखती है!
अब इस कैम्पेन से थोड़ा डरिये भी और इसका तोड़ भी सोचिये , क्योंकि बहुतो की कलम खामोश हो जाएगी। बहुतो की पत्नियाँ समझदार नहीं निकलेंगी और परिवार तबाह कर बैठेंगी - पुरुष मूर्खो की तरह खड़ा रह जाएगा! तनु श्री भारत के लाखों घरों में आग लगवाकर छुट्टी का भरपूर आनंद उठाकर विदेश वापस चली जाएगी! अब नाना पाटेकर और विवेक अग्निहोत्री जैसे लोगों को देख लीजिए यह लोग ट्विटर पर और दूसरे माध्यमों में वामपंथियों को जमकर लतियाते हैं उनके खिलाफ अचानक दो तीन महिलाएं सामने आती हैं और कहती है 25 साल पहले मेरे साथ ही उन्होंने गलत व्यवहार किया था! यह एक नया ट्रेंड जो बेहद खतरनाक है अब 20 साल पहले या 25 साल पहले ना तो कोई सुबूत बचा होगा ना ही कोई ऐसा गवाह बचा बचा होगा फिर अब आरोप लगाकर वह भी ट्विटर पर या फेसबुक पर वह महिला क्या हासिल करना चाहती है 
एक और ध्यान देने लायक बात है, ज्यादातर वही महिलाएं आरोप लगा रही है या तो जिनका घर टूट चुका है या जो वक्त की मार से बेहद मोटी और कुरूप हो चुकी है और ऐसे पुरुषों पर आरोप लगा रही हैं जो अब शांत सुखी दांपत्य जीवन बिता रहे हैं
इन्हें तीन चार शादी किये आमिर
name: Kirti Dixit

'' ऐसा गाना जो कोई भी सभ्य व्यक्ति अपने परिवार के साथ बैठकर नहीं देख सकेगा कुछ 10 साल पहले अपनी शूटिंग के दौरान हुई घटना के बाद इन्हें किसी भी फिल्म में काम मिलना बंद होने की वजह से अवसादग्रस्त होकर इन्होंने नशे का सहारा लिया जो कि बॉलीवुड की दुनिया में सामान्य बात है , फिर इन्होने स्ट्रेस से मुक्त होने के लिए अध्यात्म का सहारा लेना उचित समझा , कुछ बोद्ध धर्म से प्रभावित हुई वहां भी इनकी आत्मा को अध्यात्मिक संतुष्टि नहीं मिली , फिर इन्होने ईसाई धर्म में अध्यात्म खोजा और धर्म बदल लिया विदेश जाकर नागरिकता भी बदली पिछले 10 साल की अध्यात्म यात्रा के पश्चात मन के विकारों में कमी तो हुई नहीं विकारों ने षणयंत्र को जन्म दिया और वापस भारत में छुट्टी मनाने के बहाने से आई और विदेश से नाम का हथियार साथ में लाती है , कुछ ही दिनों में वर्षों पुरानी तनु श्री जिसे भारतीय लगभग भूल से गए थे वो प्रसिध्द हो जाती है , और आरोप लगाती है इस देश के लोगों को बुरा भला कहती है सभी को कटघरे में रखती है ! अब इस कैम्पेन से थोड़ा डरिये भी और इसका तोड़ भी सोचिये , क्योंकि बहुतो की कलम खामोश हो जाएगी। बहुतो की पत्नियाँ समझदार नहीं निकलेंगी और परिवार तबाह कर बैठेंगी - पुरुष मूर्खो की तरह खड़ा रह जाएगा ! तनु श्री भारत के लाखों घरों में आग लगवाकर छुट्टी का भरपूर आनंद उठाकर विदेश वापस चली जाएगी ! अब नाना पाटेकर और विवेक अग्निहोत्री जैसे लोगों को देख लीजिए यह लोग ट्विटर पर और दूसरे माध्यमों में वामपंथियों को जमकर लतियाते हैं उनके खिलाफ अचानक दो तीन महिलाएं सामने आती हैं और कहती है 25 साल पहले मेरे साथ ही उन्होंने गलत व्यवहार किया था ! यह एक नया ट्रेंड जो बेहद खतरनाक है अब 20 साल पहले या 25 साल पहले ना तो कोई सुबूत बचा होगा ना ही कोई ऐसा गवाह बचा बचा होगा फिर अब आरोप लगाकर वह भी ट्विटर पर या फेसबुक पर वह महिला क्या हासिल करना चाहती है एक और ध्यान देने लायक बात है , ज्यादातर वही महिलाएं आरोप लगा रही है या तो जिनका घर टूट चुका है या जो वक्त की मार से बेहद मोटी और कुरूप हो चुकी है और ऐसे पुरुषों पर आरोप लगा रही हैं जो अब शांत सुखी दांपत्य जीवन बिता रहे हैं इन्हें तीन चार शादी किये आमिर

text:
no one can prepare you for the first time he grabs you. the panic attack that ensues as your skin crawls from feeling his fingers on your body once again. no one will tell you how long it takes to get over the feeling of being violated. no one tells you that you never can and you never will. no one warns you that three years later, when you wake up from a nightmare, it will feel like you have been assaulted all over again. that sometimes when your boyfriend’s hands near your neck, you want to cry, but you fake a moan instead.

no one will tell you that you will never forget that night. that you will never forget his face. the sounds of your screams as you begged him to stop. or the feeling of his hands forcing themselves on your body, pulling at you, scarring you for years to come.

no one will prepare you for the accusations. the lies. the threats. the questions about your character or your choice of clothing. no one will tell you about the injustice. the silence. the lack of consequence.

no one will tell you that you will have to fight like hell to prove it. this is who you are now. a walking statistic. just another number with a pulse. you’re not unique. this happens every day to thousands of women. and you’re just like them. that’s what people will tell you. but no one will tell you the truth. no one will prepare you.

text: my lovely and wonderful friend @jackiejoymanely_inspired helped me change it up a little. we took out some dark and brought in the light. here’s a little before and after along with a little inspo for this lovely friday. let’s start taking care of ourselves without feeling guilty. this is something i am starting to work on. telling myself i am not being selfish to take a little time for myself , doing things that make me feel beautiful and happy. we give so much of ourselves to our jobs, home life and our kids that we tend to forget about us and our mental health and well being. so take some time for you. get you hair, nails, lashes or whatever done. go get coffee with a friend or by yourself. take some time to disconnect from life and reconnect with your inner self.  #maketimeforyou #youarenotbeingselfish

text: helena är programledare på en av de stora tv-kanalerna och befinner sig mitt i en brytpunkt. livet har inte riktigt blivit som hon tänkt sig och jobbmässigt tvingas hon till en förändring som hon inte är beredd på. samtidigt drar metoo-rörelsen som en våg över hela världen och den påverkar även helenas liv på flera sätt. boken beskriver på ett ärligt och fint sätt svårigheten med att befinna sig mellan två tillstånd och helenas sätt att hantera detta är att skriva ner sina drömmar i en speciell drömdagbok. att låta tankens kraft styra livet i rätt riktning. berättelsen griper tag i läsaren och det är svårt att släppa den ifrån sig. trots att boken behandlar svåra ämnen som livskris och hjärtesorg och en förlegad kvinnosyn så infinner sig en känsla av hopp och framtidstro hos läsaren.  drömdagboken av agneta sjödin @agnetasjodin är feelgood som inte lämnar någon oberörd! som läsare kan jag bara säga tack! 🙏🏻❤️ ✨nu ska jag skriva min egen drömdagbok. 📕🌈🦋#drömdagboken #agnetasjödin #vågadrömmastort #metoo #tankenskraft #kvinnorikulturen #kulturladiesutmaning2018 #linda37 #ulrica175

text_retweet:
#repost @nattashasingh with @get_repost
・・・
so while i have had my #metoo experiences which most who don’t have powerful parents from the particular industry go thru that is not what this post is about ..
.i said no every single time and with god’s blessing each time i was allowed to leave without even a nail being touched...(of course i never got those projects )....
i am in support of people who speak up for justice wether it be a man or a woman......anyone who wants to work in a line that is their passion should be allowed to work on merit of talent and hard work 🙏🏻
i have known guys who have gone thru it too!
sexual misconduct is not only toward women....
also i have seen quite a few women willing to do anything to make it.....and somewhere i do wish they,d stop so that everyone had a fair chance and then men would maybe not presume all women are willing ....
and i have also met many good people in this line too...respectable and respecting people who never ever crossed the line 🙏🏻and even though i was told i’d never make it by people i said no to i did work with my values intact (whatever little work i have done )...
but even though my experiences were nothing compared to the horrific cases i’m reading about i still developed an anxiety and panic attack problem because of everything i saw from a young age ...
at one point my panic and anxiety was so bad that for the longest time i couldn’t even go to an office for a meeting if the producer or director was a man!.
so this post is about being an anxiety and panic attack survivor 🤘🏻 ....#im #notashamed nor should you be if you suffer from #panic #anxiety #stress or #depression .
i healed fully and so can you🙏🏻🌈💞💞
p.s pls be kind to people speaking up about their traumas ...it takes guts and a long time to heal mentally and emotionally !🙏🏻
#worldmentalhealthday #mentalhealth #healing #kindness #compassion #mentalhealthmatters #natashasingh #nattashasingh 
in support of #notashamed #mentalhealthawareness #panicattacks #hopeithelps

text: i know my post yesterday was really heavy but it was also incredibly necessary, for me and all the other women out there that needed to see it. the amount of women that wrote me to tell me they had similar experiences when they were younger/in high school was astounding and while it makes my heart heavy to hear those stories i also felt incredibly honored to have been told them, so thank you, from the bottom of my heart. let's all take a moment to stand and raise our glass to every one of the profoundly amazing women of this world. i have no doubt that we will take this place by the shoulders, shake it with our ferocious strength and change it for the better, one story at a time. because you and i, we belong to a sisterhood that can never be broken. i love you all with every ounce of my being and i am so proud to be part of that sisterhood 👵🏽👩🏾‍⚕️👩🏿‍🎓👩🏻‍🏫👩🏽‍⚖👩🏼‍🔧👩🏻‍💼👩🏿‍🔬👳🏽‍♀️🧕🏾 #believewomen #womensreality #believesurvivors #metoo #whyididntreport #imwithher #timesup #womenoftheworld #sisterhood #momentsinmotherhood #inspiremothers #honestlymothering #parenthood_unveiled #memoirsofmotherhood #therealparenthood #theeverymother #badasssmothers

text:
you asked me how i feel about my harassment. its really difficult to put it into words.
i feel like cutting those parts of my body that has ever been touched. i feel like a filthy whore because someone has touched me. 
i spend my nights wide awake at night staring at my ceiling, reliving the moment he pushed himself inside me without my permission and how much did it hurt. how it destroyed not only my body but my soul aswell.

no one will tell you about the nightmares. the constant fear. how you won’t be able to walk down a street at night without constantly looking over your shoulder.

no one could have prepared you for the moment he wrapped his hands around your neck and started to squeeze. the moment you started praying that maybe you would pass out so that you wouldn’t have to live through what you knew was going to happen next. wondering whether being unconscious would be better than the alternative.

no one could have prepared you for the shame you felt as you grabbed your clothes and your belongings and wnet to home, as bruises started to colour your body.

no one told you about the days that would follow. days that felt like months, and months that felt like years. days without food, or sleep, or human contact. how you would spend your days locked behind your door, hoping that the four walls of your room could protect you from the terror that was outside. hoping that maybe if you didn’t tell anyone, or see anyone, or maybe not acknowledge it that it didn’t actually happen.

text:
a live durational performance by colombian- born artist, nathalie alfonso, entitled “ underscore,” an incessant rhythm of washing away her own work that visualizes invisible labor along the facade of fair market.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non traditional venue.

text: i’ve had a second account dedicated to issues like these for a while now, but i’ve decided to merge my main with my activist account because this is who i am, these are the issues i believe in. this is what i want to see change in our world. if you don’t agree with me on some issues that’s okay, say something, speak out, comment on my post and let’s have a discussion, maybe we can both learn something through constructive debate. and if you do agree with me just know that you’re not alone. the past couple years i’ve felt really hopeless, and it’s only been magnified as of recent. there are millions of others who want to see the same productive, inclusive, positive change that you do. but that change isn’t going to happen just by scrolling through social media, reading articles and watching videos that infuriate you. ignoring those articles and videos won’t help either, the fact that some people can ignore certain issues is a privilege, recognize that. change is only going to come about through acting on your beliefs. get out there and register to vote, that goes for people on all sides of these issues. voting is our right and not everyone on this planet has that power in their government. so take advantage of it, let your opinions be heard ‘round the world, it’s waiting and listening.

text:
we aren't done folks! join us on november at the #imready conference to explore what it means to be self-identified aapi women as it relates to different forms of gender-based violence.
.
joining us is hamida yusufzai. hamida has served with banteay srei since 2016. she has also worked internationally as a community organizer, a rape crisis advocate and a consultant for law enforcement - she has a global understanding of violence against women. she currently instructs a reality based self-defense class in oakland, on her own time. she has over 15 years of experience working in youth organizing with system impacted people of color. she is an advocate for comprehensive services for commercial sexual exploitation of children (csec) and contributes to the enhancement of the intensive case management component used to address the economic and emotional needs of southeast asian young women and girls. learn more about hamida's work @banteaysreioakland
.
registration ends 10/22!! link in bio!

text:
today i took a mental health day. i'm not sick, i'm not insane, i just needed a day to put my broken pieces back in place, because although i'm strong, i'm also vulnerable, and all that is going on in terms of women's rights is a constant trigger. i'm reliving almost on a daily basis my own trauma and i just needed a day to find my balance, my inner peace, my harmony. it's important to practice self-care. remember and repeat: you are worthy, you are valuable, you are strong, you deserve respect and love.
#harmony #love #strong #selfcare #mentalhealth #trigger #metoo #respect #youareworthy #ibelieveyou #streetart #mural #lowereastside #nyc #manhattan #woman #trauma #youarenotalone #womensrights

text:
this is how we go on. 
every friday i get an email from @austinkleon. it is one of my favourite things in my inbox. i loved his steal like an artist and show your work and i look forward to the next book coming out soon. 
he inspires me to keep going, keep doing, keep giving, keep listening, keep showing up, keep writing, keep doing the work. 
what a doozy of a season. what an invitation for us to rise and rise and keep rising. 
i may go quiet for a while, i may take time out to restore and refresh. but this party is not over yet. hell, no. 
i will keep speaking up, keep leaning in, keep learning, keep unlearning, keep deconstructing, keep decolonizing, keep hoping and keep loving. 
it is no coincidence that you and i are here, at this time in history. we have beautiful and good work to do. 
reminds me of toni morrison’s words: this is precisely the time when artists go to work. there is no time for despair, no place for self-pity, no need for silence, no room for fear. we speak, we write, we do language. that is how civilizations heal.” —toni morrison 
amen.

text:
calgary artist @gretajanepaperco has started an amazing movement to send letters of encouragement to dr christine ford. @gretajanepaperco is offering free cards and stamps to those who want to send a letter of encouragement. all you have to do is send her a dm with your address. ❤️ her goal is to send as much love and positivity to dr ford during this dark time. in the 90s, anita hill, came forward with allegations against another supreme court nominee in the 90s and was met with letters of encouragement that she said comforted her and encouraged her to keep fighting. let’s offer the same support to dr ford. #believewomen #metoo .

text:
life generally brings you up to be  is right. for example when a child gives a parent or a teach some work he or she has been given the parent or the teacher quickly goes through the work to see what is wrong with it and brings those to the attention of the child. attention to what he or she got right is most not  highlighted or celebrated. this also translates to our relationships and how we relate with people in ourselves . we critic them on everything that is wrong with the people in our lives , most times not constructively and most times not celebrate or encourage what good they have brought to our lives. we are so negatively programmed we even look out for it in the media. that is why bad news and bad behavior is reported and sort after by the media and people who listens. this is not the way god wants us to be. the world would critic you and say you are weak but god says you are strong. the world would say you don't matter but god says you are the apple of my eye ( zach2:8) and i recognize your value to the extent that i know the number of hairs on your head (luke 12:7) . the world says you should be afraid but god says do not be afraid , in fact he said it 365 times in the bible , one for every day of the year. there are many more examples like that in the bible.

text:
i am so thankful 9 months ago i decided to make a tough decision. 
i left a good company that i had build sustainable residual income at for 5 years, for something that has truly given me life!! i left something that i was comfortable in, for something that has breathed excitement, belief and joy into my life. 
was it a scary jump? heck yes.... but it was all worth it! 
i am inspired daily to pursue better, and to achieve my goals and dreams. 
i am surrounded by the most incredible people, and have met some of my best friends in the process. 
don’t settle for good,
pursue greatness. 
don’t settle for comfort 
pursue scary, hard, and fear ! 
it is on the other side of the great unknown, where greatness lies ! 
@justpruvit

text:
ever since the #metoo movement began, and i have been reading harrowing accounts of people and recollecting my own experiences, of sexual assaults, hurt, harm, pain, violence that we have been causing to each other, it feels like a knife ripping my chest and heart apart, and this thought has occupied my mind-are we so in control of other humans, or so not in control of ourselves, that we start doing anything and eveything with an other person?

think of this! 
aren't each of us a fragile flower? don't we want and love to be treated like one? 
nature has the answers to our issues, if only we care to look and observe. how nice would it be if we could learn the art of peaceful co-existence from them, the flowers, the leaves, the plants and the trees? 
#flowers #colours #green #pink #grass #naturephotography #peace #metoo

text:
just another training day in the books. pr for distance 💪🏼 ran hills and sprint intervals today, literally kicked my own ass. many times along the way i reminded myself of how the pain reminds me that i’m alive, and that i’m here for a reason. 
high emotions today, feeling confident and accomplished. i really wanted to lay in the grass after that run, but it’s soggy and cold so i didn’t.

so looking forward to the des moines half marathon and kicking @b.selby13 ‘s ass. my goal time is 1:55 or less. we’ll literally be within minutes of each other 🙌🏼
(apparently this is my “i just killed my run face”)😂

text:
last few days have been really disturbing for every women in india. this is because #metoo movement has finally picked up pace in here.
and i feel somewhat ambivalent about it.
though i'm extremely happy for the women who finally feel secure and confident to talk about sexual harassment sexual abuse they faced years ago. i think it's courageous of them to do this. and i
have immense amount of love and respect for each and every one of them.
but i think it's equally disturbing and disgusting how many women have gone through this shit in their life.
it's shameful that even in 21st century we are unable to provide women a safe and sound environment.
the stories we are hearing and reading are heartbreaking..
india has once again failed its women.
at the end i just wanna say one thing no matter where woman work, what work she does, what clothes she wear.
no women should be exploited. 
ending the silence!

#nomeansno
#metoo #sexualabuse #sexualharassment #indiametoomovement #women #createsafeenvironmentforwomen
#women #saynotorapes #indiawomen

text:
wir haben uns gedanken zum fall kavanaugh gemacht und was das für #metoo bedeutet: "die wahl kavanaughs hat aber auch gezeigt, dass wir als gesellschaft noch einiges zu lernen haben. dass wir zum beispiel noch viel lernen müssen, wenn wir betroffene von gewalt würdevoll behandeln wollen. momentan erfahren diese oft eine reviktimisierung durch den umgang der gesellschaft mit ihren sehr persönlichen und emotional aufwühlenden geschichten: es gibt klare gesellschaftliche vorstellungen dazu, wie sich ein «opfer» zu verhalten hat und was es leisten muss, damit es vielleicht als ein solches anerkannt wird. selbstbestimmung gehört definitiv nicht zu diesem konzept." #kavanaugh #trump #gegengewaltanfrauen #mehrmännlichkeiten #16tage #sprechenwirdarüber #opfermythos link zum ganze text in der bio

text: each artist’s work in "art as witness" addresses the issues and controversies surrounding the most polarizing presidential election and administration in recent history. timed to coincide with the final weeks of the highly anticipated #midtermelections, “art as witness” comments on the #trump presidency; the #metoo, #blacklivesmatter and #neveragain movements; the opioid epidemic; and the #guncontrol and #immigration debates to encourage engagement, spark discussion and, depending on the viewer, inspire action. “art as witness” is curated by illustrator, caricaturist and sva faculty member steve brodner and sva’s director of galleries francis di tommaso. it will be on view through saturday, november 3, at the sva chelsea gallery. #activism #protestart #schoolofvisualarts #svanyc #staywoke #vote #change #yeswecan @sva_galleries @sbrodner

text:
this is tremendously sad. when a child is abused they carry it for life. and even when they battle the demons and move forward, the experiences are set in the foundation of their development. it’s never forgotten. and no one deserves that. some don’t even get the help they need and that is even more heartbreaking. all these stories need to be heard. and justice should be brought to all victims.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my new project, our stories matter, is a way for all of us to be heard. victims of assault, abuse, and domestic violence have voices and we need to listen and support them. i’ve also teamed up with licensed psychotherapist @cosmicchristine to help provide a safe place for people to come forward and open up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text_retweet:
#repost @nattashasingh (@get_repost)
・・・
so while i have had my #metoo experiences which most who don’t have powerful parents from the particular industry go thru that is not what this post is about ..
.i said no every single time and with god’s blessing each time i was allowed to leave without even a nail being touched...(of course i never got those projects )....
i am in support of people who speak up for justice wether it be a man or a woman......anyone who wants to work in a line that is their passion should be allowed to work on merit of talent and hard work 🙏🏻
i have known guys who have gone thru it too!
sexual misconduct is not only toward women....
also i have seen quite a few women willing to do anything to make it.....and somewhere i do wish they,d stop so that everyone had a fair chance and then men would maybe not presume all women are willing ....
and i have also met many good people in this line too...respectable and respecting people who never ever crossed the line 🙏🏻and even though i was told i’d never make it by people i said no to i did work with my values intact (whatever little work i have done )...
but even though my experiences were nothing compared to the horrific cases i’m reading about i still developed an anxiety and panic attack problem because of everything i saw from a young age ...
at one point my panic and anxiety was so bad that for the longest time i couldn’t even go to an office for a meeting if the producer or director was a man!.
so this post is about being an anxiety and panic attack survivor 🤘🏻 ....#im #notashamed nor should you be if you suffer from #panic #anxiety #stress or #depression .
i healed fully and so can you🙏🏻🌈💞💞
p.s pls be kind to people speaking up about their traumas ...it takes guts and a long time to heal mentally and emotionally !🙏🏻
#worldmentalhealthday #mentalhealth #healing #kindness #compassion #mentalhealthmatters #natashasingh #nattashasingh #natasha #natasha

text:
"just get over it" they say... this is what i have to say about the #stopkavanaugh movement.. first of all, whoever put this on their vehicle in the sunset, thank you for speaking out! i feel supported i feel heard! 
i also want to take a minute and recognize a very serious issue in our world, #sexualassault and #domesticviolence  as a multiple incident survivor this topic does not come lightly for me to discuss. to me it is disturbing that it took some allegations of one person to come out in the media for people to all of a sudden start caring when its been happening for centuries. people like myself and other survivors have yelled out and spoken out and i've never received the recognition or restitution for what has happened. so shame on humanity for just now seeing the problem! if a woman comes out about what happened to her #believeher #believesurvivors it is not a joke and it is something we must carry our whole lives and fight out of our minds our whole lives. 
stop the b.s. and stand for survivors because one day it could happen to you and then what? oh and p.s. never tell a survivor to simply "get over it" if it were that easy we would.

text:
domestic violence 
in south asia, the rigid cultures and discriminatory attitudes towards women have led to the exploitation of women, from individual to community levels. women and girls in this region are exposed to biased, inequitable practices and violent behaviors at all stages of life. the high incidence of female infanticide in india, the frequent incidence of culture-specific types of violence like honor killings, acid attacks, and stove burnings in bangladesh, trafficking of women from nepal, sri-lanka and india to other regions of world, forced into prostitution and other forms of sexual violence, as well as the high prevalence of domestic violence in all countries of the region, all constitute examples of violence against women in this region. the deeply entrenched cultural norms, lead to acceptance of violence as ‘normal life experiences for a woman’ and to dispel such cultural myths and norms is a formidable task. in the family unit the man is the undisputed ruler of the household. the ineffective legislations encourage abusers to commit abusive acts against women without any repercussions. to eradicate violence against women in this region there are some fundamental challenges which include: changing existing social and individual attitudes, both at the family and societal levels, as well as implementation of policies for equity and sustaining of the political will to achieve significant results.
via
© 2013 s. karger ag, basel
#chuprahobyremal
let's take measures steps to eliminate this social evil.

text: idag har jag varit och pratat om vårt arbete med livemusikscenen i sverige, fast i norge. fantastiskt kul! tack för inbjudan @konsertarrangorer. tack publik och panel. vi kan göra skillnad med en tydlig samverkan mellan olika aktörer, med positiva exempel och perspektiv och med konkreta volontärutbildningar och tydliga kampanjer. metoo har gett oss fastare mark att ta avstamp ifrån när vi hoppar.#metoo har gett statistiken vi kunde ett ansikte och både ökat förståelsen och förändringstakten. genom kunskap om kommunikation, gränser, aktivt åskådarskap och det positiva med sexualitet kan sexualbrotten minskas. festivaler kan bidra till samhällsförändringar, vara en kraft som tar initiativ. låt oss göra det genom att sluta prata om vad vi inte ska göra, vad vi inte ska vara. låt oss istället prata om vad vi ska göra och vilka vi kan och vill vara. #daretocare #rfsu #tryggaevenemang #minbästatygkasse

text:
#metoo movement leaders tell the world that christine blasey-ford’s testimony was “not in vain”
what sacrifice, at the end of the day, did she make? hers is a story of million dollar donations, free lawyers and an event that she and the fbi know nothing of. it’s okay to support the #metoo movement (of course) but that blasey-ford appeared as a female accuser, in the way that we all witnessed, does not frankly move or impress me in the even the slightest. long story short - i do not believe her story at all. do you?

are you still thinking of "save girl child" let's start a new one "make this world a better place for girl's".
why the girls are said to behave with decency ? why the girls are stopped to wear short dresses ? why the girl are restricted not to go out of the house late night ? 
instead , why not boys are taught to behave well ? why not boys are taught to respect girls ? why are we(girls )  being punished without no reasons?
let's stop this thing . dear brother let your sister also be out of house at 10 pm fearlessly . let your sister be enjoy with their friends. let your sister also do late night parties. please i request you all to educate your child as well as  your mind and stop this thing to happen. 
from now only let's start "better world for girls " 
let our babies be born in a world where no one knows the meaning of rape, where rape is just a history .

text:
october is domestic violence awareness month. nearly 3 out of 4 people are or know someone who is affected by domestic violence. •
•
domestic violence affects both women and men, of every race, religion, culture, and socioeconomic status. it’s not just punches and black eyes—it’s yelling, humiliation, stalking, manipulation, coercion, threats, and isolation. it’s stealing a paycheck, keeping tabs online, non-stop texting, constant use of the silent treatment, or calling someone stupid so often they believe it. •
•
thehotline.org offers free, confidential chat services so you can get the help you need without saying a word. •
•
you can also speak with a 24/7 peer advocate at 866-331-9474  or text "loveis" to 22522. •
•
at the federal level, it’s time to reauthorize the violence against women act. i encourage you to join me in calling on congress—this should be a priority, and they’ve already delayed reauthorization after missing the initial expiration date. •
•
at the state level, i provided testimony earlier this year in support of hb 30: domestic violence - education and definition of abuse, sponsored by delegate angel. this bill would expand the definition of abuse to include harassment—together with written and electronic harassment—and malicious destruction of property. it would also require the state board of education to encourage county boards of education to incorporate age-appropriate lessons on domestic violence in addition to dating violence. •
•
education is a critical part of changing a culture, particularly a culture of domestic and/or sexual harassment and violence. let’s educate ourselves and push for educating our youth on positive relationships to #breakthecycle. #itsonus #dvam #dvam18 #supportsurvivors #metoo #empowerment

text:
anyone else feel like they are stuck in a horrific web of oppression right now? perhaps one they’ve been stuck in their whole lives but is so heart wrenchingly painful in the current moment as woman after woman comes forward with their stories?
🤲🏿
being a sensitive person makes it hard to stay focused during this time of uncovering a deep collective pain. i’ve been using this simple practice i learned from @tamilynnkent to stay grounded when it is all too overwhelming.
🤲🏾
▫️close your eyes, take several deep breaths and focus your energy and breath toward your center. this can be your solar plexus, your abdomen or your pelvic bowl.
▫️visualize what is stuck there, blocking energy and positivity from moving freely throughout your body.
▫️clear it out: pretend you are using your hands, a broom, a rag, or a freaking power hose and wipe whatever is not welcome away. (ok, maybe something more gentle than a power hose)
▫️once you have cleared your center, plant a seed with something you want to create. something that you are longing for.
▫️bless the space. i like to say “may i have feel whole and capable to accomplish anything i wish” “may i have the strength that i need to to get through this time with grace” or simply “i am strong” ▫️carry on with you day, a little more collected, calm and grounded.
▫️do awesome shit. be a good person. vote.
🤲🏽

text:
🚺she-roes 👑
"she needed a hero, so she became one."
. 
yesterday was international #dayofthegirl -  in my book that's every day! .
it got me thinking about this incredibly bright & loving girl, sky, whom i met last weekend.
.
she was full of life, her caring, curious, unabashed nature  reminded me of myself when i was younger.
.
i was very fortunate to grow up in a liberal household where i was taught i could be/do anything i set my heart on. .
.
sadly in today's world, for all the feminist bras that have been voraciously flung aside, the shadow of patriarchy still lingers like the dense london fog.
.
even in 2018, there's still a gender pay gap and inequality runs rife.... women and girls are constantly stereotyped and not free to express themselves without being objectified.... .
.
the #metoo movement;  98 million girls, globally, under the age of 18 that are not in school and the fact that we need to set aside 1 day to bring awareness to all of this breaks my heart. 💔
.
i implore you, brothers, respect & honour the women in your lives and sisters, be the women you would want your daughters to become by celebrating your womanhood....we are living, breathing, role models for the younger girls....let us show them they are worthy, they are loved, they are strong, they are smart and that they can become & do anything they want without feeling ashamed.
.
 we have been socialized to feel unentitled to our own space, to shrink our presence. to be feminine is to be small and contained. no girl should ever feel the need to shrink herself to be accepted.
.
it all starts with us.
.
let us blaze a trail & set and an example for all the skys out there.
.
happy #girlday everyday! 😘
.
.___________________________________
▶turn on notifications and subscribe to my blog: ▶www.thejaxblog.com for travel inspiration!✨
___________________________________
.
.

text:
बॉलीवुड में सामने आ रहे तमाम यौन शोषण और कास्टिंग काउच के मामलों पर हर किसी ने अपनी राय जाहिर की है. इस सबके बीच हाल ही में डेब्यू करने वालीं जाह्नवी कपूर ने एक सार्थक बात शेयर की, जिसे उन्होंने किसी अन्य की इंस्टाग्राम स्टोरी में पढ़ा था. जाह्नवी ने इस पोस्ट का समर्थन करते हुए कहा कि ये मीटू  के संबंध में सबसे अच्छी सलाह है. इसमें कहा गया है- यदि पुरुष सेक्सअुल असॉल्ट के झूठे मामलों को लेकर चिंतित हैं तो उन्हें घर पर ही रहना चाहिए और ऐसी खतरनाक स्थिति में नहीं कूदना चाहिए, जिसमें उन्हें नुकसान हो सकता हो. पूरी जानकारी: https://bit.ly/2iqdw6t

i've never been the pretty one. wasn't the talented one. though i had some smarts, i was never the brainy one either. from childhood even into adulthood i've always found myself never really fitting in. i was the black sheep in my family, the weird girl that was bullied in school, and the outcast in church and social settings. i felt that i tried hard to be who people wanted me to be or who they thought i should be, but i could never measure up. i was not quite pretty enough, smart enough, talented enough, connected enough, spiritual enough, rich enough, black enough... well moving forward, i'm stepping in to being me. and guess what? i am enough!

#imcomingout #therealme #findingsophie

text:
founded by tarana burke more than a decade ago, #metoo came to new prominence in october 2017 after women came forward publicly with allegations of sexual harassment and assault by harvey weinstein. in the weeks and months that followed, more and more americans shared their own stories of being harassed or assaulted in the workplace by people — most of them men — in positions of power. 
a year after those allegations, we asked activists, journalists, and others across industries to answer a single question: “what is the #metoo movement?” the answers varied, but taken together, they made clear that the movement is far from over.

read more about the state of the movement at the link in our bio — and tell us below: what is your definition?
name: Vox
tweet_full:
founded by tarana burke more than a decade ago, #metoo came to new prominence in october 2017 after women came forward publicly with allegations of sexual harassment and assault by harvey weinstein. in the weeks and months that followed, more and more americans shared their own stories of being harassed or assaulted in the workplace by people — most of them men — in positions of power. 
a year after those allegations, we asked activists, journalists, and others across industries to answer a single question: “what is the #metoo movement?” the answers varied, but taken together, they made clear that the movement is far from over.

read more about the state of the movement at the link in our bio — and tell us below: what is your definition?

text:
#fbf getting goofy with my ladies!⁣ this online coaching thing isn’t about working out...⁣
⁣
it's my therapy. it's taught me to control my mindset & my attitude.⁣
⁣
in a crazy time in our history #metoo, where women are banding together more and more in support of each other, i feel it fitting to share.⁣
⁣
it’s always been hard for me connect with other women, and beachbody coaching has really helped me bridge that gap!⁣
⁣
when i first started coaching, people assumed i did it because i "loved working out". it offended me because it's been so much more to me than that! ⁣
⁣
i don't do it for the work out. the results of the workout are a bonus.⁣
⁣
behind the scenes, it’s only one small piece of this amazing biz!⁣
⁣
i get it. i am a personal trainer. but if it wasn’t for online coaching, i wouldn’t be a trainer. #realtalk⁣
⁣
it’s not even about the money. i'm grateful to  paying off my debt faster! it's a stress-reliever ⁣
($5k extra last year from online coaching)⁣
⁣
but really? ⁣
⁣
it’s been more about the connections and the community. the friendships. the like minded chicks rooting me on. ⁣
⁣
i get to inspire and encourage others to be healthier and better versions of themselves! 🙌🙌⁣
⁣
whats could you do with the right tribe? ❤️⁣
⁣
helping others be better versions of themselves?⁣
⁣
#doneson #accountability #thatcoachlife

text: had a conversation with keira knightley today during the bfi screen talk event where i talked about gender rights and yes, i consciously used the word 'gender' because going my previous posts, you can understand that i don't like women being asked questions starting with 'as a woman' just as i wouldn't approve of a man being asked a question starting with 'as a man'. i'm rather more interested in talking about how the world restricts certain gender identities from having a voice and how to overcome it. well, i met with 'that's a good question response'. listen to this audio version of my conversation today and i'm waiting for the british film institute (bfi) to upload the official video version on its youtube channel soon. #keiraknightley #bfi #british #film #institute #colette #muneebqadir #colette #feminism #metoo #gender #discussion

text:
i know i’m a day late on this, but i wanted to post something anyway! yesterday was #worldmentalhealthday and i want to say thank you to everyone who posted and talked about mental health and provided encouragement and support! mental health is so important and sometimes you don’t realize it until your own mental health demands to be noticed.
.
.
it’s about to get really personal (so thanks for reading): i don’t know about any of you, but everything going on in the news with the kavanaugh stuff has been really hard for me. i am a survivor myself and i’ve already been in counseling trying to work through my own experience and find healing. then two weeks ago it seemed like everyone and their mother was talking about this issue and expressing their opinions. i have very strong views about it all, but i’m also just trying to work through what happened to me and the ways it’s affected me, even now over a decade later. the last two weeks have resurfaced pain that i’d buried deep and tried to forget. my counseling has been picking up lately too, so it’s just been rough. my anxiety has been at an all time high the last several weeks and i’m so ready to move past all this, which is so much easier said than done. however, i’m so thankful that i have a lot of amazing people in my life who believe me, love me and support me, as well as a faithful and gracious god who comes through time and time again! 💕
.
.
anyway, there’s so much i could say but i’ll leave you with some resources instead:
✨the national suicide prevention lifeline is 1-800-283-8254. you can also chat online at suicidepreventionlifeline.org/chat/
✨this article has a great list of resources on mental health! time.com/money/4607786/mental-health-costs-resources-help/
✨the national sexual assault hotline is 1-800-656-4673. you can also chat online at hotline.rainn.org/online/
✨you can find more resources about how to get help if you’re a survivor of sexual assault at nsvrc.org/find-help
.
.
thanks for listening, friends! i hope you’re all having a great day and making time to take care of yourself!! ❤️
p.s. i posted this with a picture of crochet because that’s my go to self-care activity! what’s yours?

text:
hot news
nana patekar keluar dari proyek housefull 4 setelah ultimatum akshay kumar penundaan syuting 😐

aktor nana patekar dilaporkan keluar dari housefull 4 di tengah tuduhan pelecehan seksual terhadap dirinya oleh tanushree dutta. juga dugaan sutradara film, sajid khan untuk penyelidikan perihal yang sama. nana patekar bereaksi ketika berbicara dengan media di mumbai.

menurut laporan media keputusan nana muncul setelah bintang akshay kumar, mengatakan dia tidak akan bekerja dengan pelanggar seksual yang terbukti. akshay menulis di twitter bahwa ia telah meminta produser film itu untuk menghentikan produksi film tersebut, sambil menunggu penyelidikan. pernyataan akshay datang setelah tuduhan serupa dibuat terhadap sutradara film itu, sajid khan. "ini adalah sesuatu yang membutuhkan tindakan keras. saya tidak akan bekerja dengan pelanggar yang terbukti dan mereka yang ditundukkan untuk pelecehan harus didengar dan diberikan keadilan yang pantas mereka terima", tulis akshay.

sajid khan sendiri mengumumkan bahwa dia akan mengundurkan diri sebagai sutradara untuk menghilangkan semua tuduhan dan membuktikan kebenaran. nana, sementara itu, membantah semua tuduhan yang dilontarkan terhadapnya. itu adalah pernyataan tanushree dutta bahwa pemenang penghargaan nasional telah melecehkannya di set film "horn ok pleassss" tahun 2008 yang memacu gerakan #metoo india. nana telah mengajukan gugatan pencemaran nama baik terhadapnya, setelah itu tanushree menamparnya dengan laporan tuduhan.

beberapa hari setelah klaim tanushree, saudara perempuan sajid, sutradara dan koreografer farah khan, berpose dengan nana di sebuah foto instagram. farah sekarang mengatakan bahwa tuduhan terhadap kakaknya terbukti benar, dia harus menebus dosa-dosanya. farah menulis di twitter, “ini adalah waktu yang memilukan bagi keluarga saya. kami harus bekerja melalui beberapa masalah yang sangat sulit. jika saudara laki-lakiku bertingkah laku seperti ini, dia punya banyak hal untuk ditebus. aku sama sekali tidak mendukung perilaku ini dan berdiri dalam solidaritas dengan wanita mana pun yang terluka”. #hindustantimes 
#bollywoodnews
#bollywoodindonesia
#nanapatekar

text_retweet:
here is our co-founder, sanat pandit, providing a peak into the mind of a #metoo survivor.
・・・
#repost @synikus
・・・
“don’t cry, stop the salt flow. 
hear me out now. 
you wound my coil tight. 
why won’t you smile?” no words were spoken, but my body apparently lied.
you waited, for hours, while i “teased”
i can’t get inside your head, but i never really welcomed you in tonight. 
touching my soft skin, slipping your hands below my waist, you unwound inside me, bringing your ragged breath to a calm. 
in my flailing arms, spilling the colours of your dark. 
but your pleasure and my pain have rendered our eyes blind. 
now, in my heart, there’s a hole. 
just horrible scars where my wings used to reside. 
i am scared of the night, clinging to the rays, hoping they never slip away 
for it brings alive the demons that you’ve branded on my soul. 
for no mistake of mine, i’m the slut, the whore. 
blame it on the clothes or the spirit, but it’s just you and your wretched mind. 
it’s never okay, it is always a fucking crime. .
.

text:
bless your heart, william.

this anger/violence towards justice for rape victims (sweepingly hates sjws for standing up) proves his guilt. we don't know the details, but this is classic lashing out.  he continues to persecute victims. even if he himself never harmed a single woman, he's certainly harming them now, and the way he responds to sexual assault allegations and the discourse surrounding abuse is wrong and stinks text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if you’re waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isn’t forthcoming. what most of them haven’t lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it. 
#nomore #speakupagainstadamcroasdell

text_retweet:
i am doing dressember again this year!!! join me? 
#repost @dressember with @get_repost
・・・
despite the claim of the president of the bangladesh garment manufacturers and exporters association that sexual harassment doesn’t exist in garment factories in bangladesh, according to fashion revolution, statistics show around 60% of bangladeshi garment workers have suffered from sexual harassment. about 75 million people work directly in the fashion and textiles industry and about 80% of them are women. many are subject to exploitation and verbal and physical abuse. we have to remember that #metoo doesn't just apply to celebrities, ceos, and politicians. it is present wherever women are made vulnerable and voiceless, including the factories in which our clothes are made. to learn more, check out @fash_rev and their fashion transparency index 2018, which reviews and ranks 150 major global brands and retailers and throws a spotlight on how brands and retailers are tackling gender-based discrimination and violence in supply chains.
_

text:
words cannot express how proud i am of my friend and business partner betsy. 
ladies, we need to share our stories and speak our truth... even when your voice shakes. 
vulnerability is not weakness. it’s the exact opposite. only the strongest among us will dare to speak in the face of opposition, judgment, recrimination or even hate. 
what does it mean to stand in your truth?

it is easy, when things feel hard or insurmountable, to hide behind our stories. 
we end up presenting only a part of ourselves to the world, the part that we think the world wants to hear or the one that "makes sense". but is that really enough?

in today's solo episode, betsy is sitting down to share her story—her true story—not the story she's hidden behind for the last 20 years.

it's the story that has shaped who she is, how she shows up in the world and illustrates that when you stand in your truth, you have the power to rewrite old stories and transform your life. .
============= .
.
here’s what you’ll learn in this episode: .
.
💜 the story that betsy hid behind up until today [ 5:40 ] .
.
💎 what we can do when women boldly open up and share their truth [ 6:57 ] .
.
💜 how betsy’s story influences her actions in business every day [ 11:01 ] .
.
click the link in bio to listen to today’s powerful podcast episode. 
and if you feel called to, i invite you to share this post with any women you love: friend, sister, mother, daugther. .
.

if even one women can heal from hearing this, then it’s worth asking and it’s worth sharing. 
xo ✊🏻💜

text:
last week we announced our holistic healing retreat, and are overwhelmed with the amount of love, support, and inquired about on the mend. below are answers to a few of the most common questions we’ve received.
•
do you offer a payment plan? yes.
•
how many spots are available? 9 (and we anticipate they will go fast!)
•
is it required that i have gotten some kind of treatment/therapy before i sign up for your retreat? no. but we do screen every person to ensure the details about what we offer are clear and to uphold the most comfortable, safe space for everyone attending.
•
if you have more questions, please reach out to us! we are here to support you however we can, and hope you’ll join us for this amazing healing retreat next march.
•
•
•
•
•

text:
disappear. maybe there is nothing at all. i lost myself. i can not call, express emotions. i can not ask for help. nobody taught me that. i'm ashamed of my weakness. inside, i begged for someone to take care of me, that someone would notice how i suffer and how helpless or powerless i am. today i would give everything for understanding. i believed in beautiful words. it's nothing. it is easy to get lost between sighs.
i shattered my heart against the floor. i lost everything. my world was silent. this is too bright. #ptsd #depression #therapy #mentalhealth #help #helpme #suicide #support #psychology #thoughts #survivor #awareness  #fight #talk #abuse #sexualabuse #rape #victim #metoo

text:
tw: mention of sexual assault/rape

to those who think when i choose to speak up matters.//▪️ hi. the fact that you think this way means that you have never known what it is to feel violated, broken, breathless. and i hope you never do.
because there’s nothing that can make you lose belief in the power and authenticity of the words uttered by your tongue than the fact that someone completely ignored your ‘no’. because the fact that you said it clearly, and loudly, and the apparent human being standing in front of you behaved like it meant nothing means, that sometimes, you lose faith in the ability of syllables to form meaning. and sometimes, it may take a while to believe that words can be powerful, again. how can i be expected to have spoken up at that exact moment?
because you are never done greiving over somebody ignoring your agency over your own self. you may sit for hours and cry and shout and take long hot showers to rub off the phantom of his touch from a body that does not belong to him- and feels like it doesn’t belong to you either right now- but one day, years later, you’ll be dancing at a pub celebrating your friend’s graduation and a man with a similar smirk will stare at your legs. you will freeze. you will gasp for breath. memories that you didn’t even know had been kept safe by your brain at the back of your thoughts will play in your head like a highlight reel. and you will have to go through the entire process of getting over them, again. how can i be told that it’s been too long when it happens to me again, and again, and again?//1
(contd. in the next post) .
.

¿qué tanto influyen los libros que leemos en los libros que escribimos? lolita secreta tal vez sea un interesante caso de estudio. la historia dice que havelock ellis, pionero en la medicalización de la vida sexual, tuvo acceso a este manuscrito al escribir sus estudios de psicología sexual —el texto le llegó de manos del autor, víctor, un ucraniano burgués de inicios del siglo xx. los folios quedaron adscritos al tratado como un apéndice sobre desviaciones sexuales, pero nada más. seis años antes de la publicación de la lolita de nabokov, edmund wilson le envió al ruso las páginas de este libro. nabokov contestó: “disfruté enormemente con la vida amorosa del ruso. es increíblemente divertida. ¡qué enorme suerte tuvo, siendo chico, al dar con chicas de reacciones tan inusualmente rápidas y generosas!”.
el manuscrito, por supuesto, está lleno de detalles sexuales: es, al mismo tiempo, un retrato bufonesco y el mea culpa de una vida cambiada por el erotismo. ¿de qué trata el libro, exactamente? después de que el autor nos lleva de la mano por su despertar sexual, se nos presenta una situación inusual en italia: “las dos chiquillas eran igualmente sabias; me ofrecieron información sobre la pederastia y el amor lésbico en su ciudad, practicaban ellas mismas este último, entre ellas y con amigas, habían asistido a copulaciones refinadas (entre otras, al coito de una mujer con un perro, de un hombre con un pato, al que cortó el cuello durante el acto, a coitos combinados de varias personas en pirámide), habían posado para fotografías obscenas, etc”. la pederastia en el contexto burgués (de rusia, en el caso de víctor x, o de la clase media americana, en el caso de nabokov) deviene como última frontera. esto, ante la luz de movimientos como el #metoo, hace mucho más problemática la lectura de estos textos —en otras palabras, ¿cómo hay que leer estas confesiones? ¿bajo su intención picaresca? ¿por sus méritos estilísticos? ¿como una prueba más de los ejercicios del poder patriarcal?
.
.
#libros📚 #bookstagram #literatura #lectura #leer #librosymas #librosrecomendados #libros

text:
it's #blackfriday. (check out @glennondoyle for more details.)
.
it's a dark time in our country. it's confusing and there's more grey area than ever.
.
i'm not perfect but i stand for what is right. i stand for women. i stand for people of color. i stand for lgbtqi+. i stand for students; all of my students.
.
you know how we holler at celebrities to use their platform for good? well, we as teachers have a platform too, and we need to do the same.
.
i love my students and they love me. the relationships we build are the foundation of everything we can do in school. it's more important to teach the child then to teach the subject, and that includes having a classroom where everyone is welcomed and loved. 💜

ನಾನು ಪತ್ನಿಗಿಂತ ಮುನ್ನ ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆ, ತಪ್ಪಿತಸ್ಥರಿಗೆ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗ್ಲೇಬೇಕು: ಮಯೂರಿ

#metoo ಅಭಿಯಾನದ ಏಳು ಹೆಡೆ ಸರ್ಪ ಘಟಾನುಘಟಿಗಳನ್ನು ಸುತ್ತಿಕೊಳ್ತಿದೆ. ಅದಕ್ಕೆ ಹಾಲಿವುಡ್, ಬಾಲಿವುಡ್, ಸ್ಯಾಂಡಲ್​ವುಡ್, ಕಾಲಿವುಡ್​​​, ರಾಜಕೀಯ, ಕ್ರೀಡೆ, ಸಾಹಿತ್ಯ, ಸಂಗೀತ ಹೀಗೆ ಪ್ರತಿಯೊಂದು ಕ್ಷೇತ್ರದ ಸಾಧಕರು, ಘಟಾನುಘಟಿಗಳು ಹೊರತಾಗಿಲ್ಲ. ಇದೇ #metoo ಸರ್ಪ ಇದೀಗ ಕನ್ನಡದ ರಾಷ್ಟ್ರೀಯ ಖ್ಯಾತಿಯ ಗಾಯಕ, ಸಂಗೀತ ನಿರ್ದೇಶಕ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ವಿರುದ್ಧವೂ ಭುಸ್​​ಗುಡುತ್ತಿದೆ. ಅವರ ವಿರುದ್ಧವೂ ತಮಿಳಿನ ಖ್ಯಾತ ಗಾಯಕಿ ಚಿನ್ಮಯೀ ಶ್ರೀಪಾದ್ ಗಾಯಕಿಯೊಬ್ಬರಿಗೆ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ಕಿರುಕುಳ ನೀಡಿದ್ದ ಆರೋಪ ಮಾಡಿದ್ದು, ಅದಕ್ಕೆ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ಪ್ರತ್ಯುತ್ತರ ನೀಡಿದ್ದೂ ಗೊತ್ತೇ ಇದೆ. ಈಗ ಈ ವಿವಾದಕ್ಕೆ ಸಂಬಂಧಿಸಿದಂತೆ ಗಾಯಕ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ಪತ್ನಿ ಮಯೂರಿ ಉಪಾಧ್ಯಾಯ ಟ್ವೀಟ್​ ಮಾಡಿದ್ದು, #metoo  ಅಭಿಯಾನಕ್ಕೆ ಸಂಪೂರ್ಣ ಬೆಂಬಲ ನೀಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ಅಷ್ಟೇ ಅಲ್ಲ, ತಪ್ಪಿತಸ್ಥರು ಯಾರೇ ಆಗಿದ್ರೂ ಕಾನೂನಾತ್ಮಕ ರೀತಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗಲೇ ಬೇಕು ಅಂತಾ ಆಗ್ರಹಿಸಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ತಮ್ಮ ಸಾಮಾಜಿಕ ಜಾಲತಾಣ ಟ್ವಿಟರ್​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಸರಣಿ ಟ್ವೀಟ್ ಮಾಡಿರೋ ಮಯೂರಿ, ಇಲ್ಲಿ ನನ್ನ ಮದುವೆ ಮತ್ತು ಡೈವೋರ್ಸ್​ ವಿಚಾರ ಅಪ್ರಸ್ತುತ. ನಾನು ಪತ್ನಿಯಾಗುವುದಕ್ಕಿಂತ ಮುಂಚೆ ಮಹಿಳೆ. ಅವರು ಸೆಲೆಬ್ರಿಟಿ ಇರಲಿ ಅಥವಾ ಇಲ್ಲದೇ ಇರಲಿ ಪ್ರತಿಯೊಬ್ಬರ ಡಿಗ್ನಿಟಿ ಅತ್ಯಂತ ಮುಖ್ಯ. ಈ ಘಟನೆಯ ಸತ್ಯಾಸತ್ಯತೆ ಬಗ್ಗೆ ನನಗೆ ಗೊತ್ತಿಲ್ಲ. ಆದ್ರೆ, ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆ ಹೊರ ಬಂದು ಈ ರೀತಿ ಆರೋಪ ಮಾಡಲು ಅತ್ಯಂತ ಧೈರ್ಯ ಬೇಕು ಅಂತಾ ಅವರು ಹೇಳಿದ್ದಾರೆ.
name: C I N E M A   S P O O R T H I

stop_filter_tweet: ﻿ ನಾನು ಪತ್ನಿಗಿಂತ ಮುನ್ನ ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆ , ತಪ್ಪಿತಸ್ಥರಿಗೆ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗ್ಲೇಬೇಕು : ಮಯೂರಿ ಅಭಿಯಾನದ ಏಳು ಹೆಡೆ ಸರ್ಪ ಘಟಾನುಘಟಿಗಳನ್ನು ಸುತ್ತಿಕೊಳ್ತಿದೆ . ಅದಕ್ಕೆ ಹಾಲಿವುಡ್ , ಬಾಲಿವುಡ್ , ಸ್ಯಾಂಡಲ್​ವುಡ್ , ಕಾಲಿವುಡ್​​​ , ರಾಜಕೀಯ , ಕ್ರೀಡೆ , ಸಾಹಿತ್ಯ , ಸಂಗೀತ ಹೀಗೆ ಪ್ರತಿಯೊಂದು ಕ್ಷೇತ್ರದ ಸಾಧಕರು , ಘಟಾನುಘಟಿಗಳು ಹೊರತಾಗಿಲ್ಲ . ಇದೇ ಸರ್ಪ ಇದೀಗ ಕನ್ನಡದ ರಾಷ್ಟ್ರೀಯ ಖ್ಯಾತಿಯ ಗಾಯಕ , ಸಂಗೀತ ನಿರ್ದೇಶಕ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ವಿರುದ್ಧವೂ ಭುಸ್​​ಗುಡುತ್ತಿದೆ . ಅವರ ವಿರುದ್ಧವೂ ತಮಿಳಿನ ಖ್ಯಾತ ಗಾಯಕಿ ಚಿನ್ಮಯೀ ಶ್ರೀಪಾದ್ ಗಾಯಕಿಯೊಬ್ಬರಿಗೆ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ಕಿರುಕುಳ ನೀಡಿದ್ದ ಆರೋಪ ಮಾಡಿದ್ದು , ಅದಕ್ಕೆ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ಪ್ರತ್ಯುತ್ತರ ನೀಡಿದ್ದೂ ಗೊತ್ತೇ ಇದೆ . ಈಗ ಈ ವಿವಾದಕ್ಕೆ ಸಂಬಂಧಿಸಿದಂತೆ ಗಾಯಕ ರಘು ದೀಕ್ಷಿತ್ ಪತ್ನಿ ಮಯೂರಿ ಉಪಾಧ್ಯಾಯ ಟ್ವೀಟ್​ ಮಾಡಿದ್ದು , ಅಭಿಯಾನಕ್ಕೆ ಸಂಪೂರ್ಣ ಬೆಂಬಲ ನೀಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ . ಅಷ್ಟೇ ಅಲ್ಲ , ತಪ್ಪಿತಸ್ಥರು ಯಾರೇ ಆಗಿದ್ರೂ ಕಾನೂನಾತ್ಮಕ ರೀತಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗಲೇ ಬೇಕು ಅಂತಾ ಆಗ್ರಹಿಸಿದ್ದಾರೆ . ತಮ್ಮ ಸಾಮಾಜಿಕ ಜಾಲತಾಣ ಟ್ವಿಟರ್​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಸರಣಿ ಟ್ವೀಟ್ ಮಾಡಿರೋ ಮಯೂರಿ , ಇಲ್ಲಿ ನನ್ನ ಮದುವೆ ಮತ್ತು ಡೈವೋರ್ಸ್​ ವಿಚಾರ ಅಪ್ರಸ್ತುತ . ನಾನು ಪತ್ನಿಯಾಗುವುದಕ್ಕಿಂತ ಮುಂಚೆ ಮಹಿಳೆ . ಅವರು ಸೆಲೆಬ್ರಿಟಿ ಇರಲಿ ಅಥವಾ ಇಲ್ಲದೇ ಇರಲಿ ಪ್ರತಿಯೊಬ್ಬರ ಡಿಗ್ನಿಟಿ ಅತ್ಯಂತ ಮುಖ್ಯ . ಈ ಘಟನೆಯ ಸತ್ಯಾಸತ್ಯತೆ ಬಗ್ಗೆ ನನಗೆ ಗೊತ್ತಿಲ್ಲ . ಆದ್ರೆ , ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆ ಹೊರ ಬಂದು ಈ ರೀತಿ ಆರೋಪ ಮಾಡಲು ಅತ್ಯಂತ ಧೈರ್ಯ ಬೇಕು ಅಂತಾ ಅವರು ಹೇಳಿದ್ದಾರೆ .

text: october is domestic violence awareness month and throughout the month we will be sharing some facts and unsettling statistics on the widespread impact of domestic violence in our world. we believe in bringing about awareness and change and helping victims get safe and get their lives back. thank you to @ncadv for sharing these statistics. if you or someone you know is a victim of domestic violence, please reach out. if you are in the indianapolis or surrounding areas you can contact @shelteringwings or @beacon.of.hope.indy. their trained staff can offer safety, support and education to help you become free and self-sufficient. #domesticviolenceawareness

text:
nigerian author and renowned feminist chimamanda ngozi adichie spoke at the frankfurt book fair on tuesday and touched on the #metoo movement.
.
adichie said at the opening of the world’s biggest publishing event:
.
all over the world today, women are speaking up. their stories are still not really heard.

women are still invisible. women’s experiences are still invisible.
.
a year after the #metoo movement went viral and ignited a global discussion about sexual harassment, adichie said there was much work left to be done.
.
it is time for us to pay more than lip service to the fact that women’s stories are for everyone.

#lagos #lagosnigeria #feminism #davinadiaries
