text: you couldn’t tell but it is sunny in milan. it was such an honour to be with @gucci today and listen to some young creative leaders talk about grassroots activism and whether there is ever space for brands within that. the panel was raw and honest and i couldnt be more shocked and delighted to be directing something special here too. after coming back to europe, i was so haunted by the happenings of the supreme court in america. with #metoo, it felt like the old systems were just regurgitating and reproducing themselves for all to see. today, i felt a little starstruck to hear the humility and heartfeltness that @sarahchadwick.k one of the founders of @marchforourlives carries herself with. the future doesn’t have to ruined if we responsibly listen and fight back against it. i realised the old systems can run scared if we enable different voices to keep challenging the system together and remind ourselves that we, hopefully, are seeing the dying screams of old ideas. from understanding white privilege to @tanyacompas talking about representation of queer black women and the youth, i’ve never been so awestruck and delighted to be standing with some amazing humans. @chimeforchange

text:
i think almost every woman (if not all) can admit we have at one point in our lives been sexually assaulted. 
i was 15 working in a pizzeria, my first ever job. i was one of only two women working there. sexual jokes were normal for them. i wore shorts on the first day because it was hot outside so i knew it would be hot in the kitchen, that’s when the harassment started. from that point on i wore pants, but the harassment continued. then one day i walked into the walk in cooler where my manager followed behind, and when i bent over to pick up a bag of cheese, he grabbed my hips and humped me. he had to be in his late 30’s. at that point, i quit, i called my dad and i waited outside until my dad picked me up.

i was 15. and there are more that’s happened since then. but this is the one i’ve saved in my memory box. this is not okay. this has never been okay. we need to protect our daughters, we need to teach our sons, we need to start a conversation. #sexualassualt #sexualabuse #survivor #youniquefoundation #nomore #metoo
name: Liz Marciniak

i was 15. and there are more that’s happened since then. but this is the one i’ve saved in my memory box. this is not okay. this has never been okay. we need to protect our daughters, we need to teach our sons, we need to start a conversation. #sexualassualt #sexualabuse #survivor #youniquefoundation #nomore #metoo

text:
i often hear victims of domestic abuse telling me why they “can’t” leave.  one of the most common reasons is: children. “but the kids...” “we have kids...”
let me put another spin on this for you. the two questions i always follow up with....let these sink in, please.
• would you want your son to treat his spouse this way?
• would you be okay with your daughter being treated this way?
(or vice versa, y’all. dv does not discriminate gender.) make these precious babies your reason to get out. your job is to protect them, and show them just how strong and badass you truly are. 📷: @raelynramey #wmnuprising 
#dvam #thenewgeneration #bethechange #domesticviolenceawareness #survivor #ibelieveyou #metoo #supportsurvivors #momlife #domesticviolence

inte du , iaf , därav ditt förakt mot mig och försvarsmekanismerna din analys som gör mig till ett objekt hellre än lika värd .

entertainment | #metoo: sajid khan steps down as ‘housefull 4’ director

details: sajid khan has stepped down as the director of upcoming comedy-drama ‘housefull 4’ after being accused of sexual harassment by three women.

taking to social media, khan wrote, “in the wake of allegations against me and the pressure being put on my family, my producers and the stars of my film housefull 4, i must take the moral responsibility of stepping down from my directorial post, till the time i can allay the allegations and prove the truth. i request my friends in the media to kindly not pass judgment till the truth is out.” #metooindia #sajidkhan #bollywood #bollywoodcelebs #entertainmentnews #india #pratidintime

text: #metoo ಅಭಿಯಾನದ ಬಗ್ಗೆ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಹೇಳಿದ್ದೇನು..? #metoo ಅಭಿಯಾನದಿಂದ ಆರೋಪಿತರ (ದೊಡ್ದವರ) ಹೆಸರುಗಳು ಬಹಿರಂಗೊಳುತ್ತಿವೆ. ಇದರಿಂದ ಖುಷಿಯಾಗುತ್ತಿದೆ. ಈ ಅಭಿಯಾನ ಒಂದು ಗೇಮ್ ಚೇಂಜರ್​​ ಎಂದು ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಅಭಿಪ್ರಾಯಪಟ್ಟಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ಹುಬ್ಬಳ್ಳಿ ನಗರದಲ್ಲಿ ಜುವೆಲರಿ ಶೋ ಉದ್ಘಾಟಿಸಿದ ಬಳಿಕ ಮಾಧ್ಯಮಗಳೊಂದಿಗೆ ಮಾತನಾಡಿದ ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ, ಈಗಲಾದ್ರು ಮಹಿಳೆಯರು ಧ್ವನಿ ಎತ್ತುತ್ತಿರುವದು ಸ್ವಾಗತಾರ್ಹ. ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆಗೆ ತನ್ನ ಮೇಲಾದ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ಸಹಿಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳುವದು‌ ಕಷ್ಟಕರ ಸಂಗತಿ. ಸತ್ಯ ಯಾವಾಗ ಹೇಳಿದರೂ ಅದು ಸತ್ಯವೇ ಆಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ. ಆರೋಪಿಗಳೆಲ್ಲರಿಗೂ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗದಿದ್ದರೂ, ಕೆಲವರಿಗಾದರೂ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆಯಾಗಲಿ ಅನ್ನೋದು ನಮ್ಮ ಆಶಯ. ಇದರಿಂದಾಗಿ ಮುಂದಿನ ದಿನಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ಮಾಡುವವರು ವಿಚಾರ ಮಾಡುವಂತಾಗುತ್ತದೆ. ಇದೆಲ್ಲವೂ ಮೀಡಿಯಾಗಳಿಂದ ಸೆನ್ಸೇಷನಲ್ ಆಗುತ್ತಿವೆ ಎಂದು ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಹೇಳಿದರು. ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯದಲ್ಲಿ ಗಂಡು ಮತ್ತು ಹೆಣ್ಣಿನ ಪ್ರಶ್ನೆ ಬರಲ್ಲ. ಅಧಿಕಾರ ಬಲ ಹಾಗೂ ಹಣಬಲದಿಂದ ಇಂತ ಕೃತ್ಯ ನಡೆಯುತ್ತಿವೆ. ಇದನ್ನು ತಡೆಯುವ ನಿಟ್ಟಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಚಲಚಿತ್ರ ವಾಣಿಜ್ಯ ಮಂಡಳಿಗಳೂ ಕೂಡಾ ಕಾಳಜಿವಹಿಸುತ್ತಿವೆ. #metoo ಅಭಿಯಾನದಲ್ಲಿ ಕವಿತಾ ಲಂಕೇಶ್​ ಹಾಗೂ ನಾನು ಸೇರಿದಂತೆ ಹಲವರು ಭಾಗಿಯಾಗಿ ಧ್ವನಿ ಎತ್ತಲಿದ್ದೇವೆ ಎಂದರು.

stop_filter_tweet: ಅಭಿಯಾನದ ಬಗ್ಗೆ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಹೇಳಿದ್ದೇನು.. ? ಅಭಿಯಾನದಿಂದ ಆರೋಪಿತರ ( ದೊಡ್ದವರ ) ಹೆಸರುಗಳು ಬಹಿರಂಗೊಳುತ್ತಿವೆ . ಇದರಿಂದ ಖುಷಿಯಾಗುತ್ತಿದೆ . ಈ ಅಭಿಯಾನ ಒಂದು ಗೇಮ್ ಚೇಂಜರ್​​ ಎಂದು ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಅಭಿಪ್ರಾಯಪಟ್ಟಿದ್ದಾರೆ . ಹುಬ್ಬಳ್ಳಿ ನಗರದಲ್ಲಿ ಜುವೆಲರಿ ಶೋ ಉದ್ಘಾಟಿಸಿದ ಬಳಿಕ ಮಾಧ್ಯಮಗಳೊಂದಿಗೆ ಮಾತನಾಡಿದ ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ , ಈಗಲಾದ್ರು ಮಹಿಳೆಯರು ಧ್ವನಿ ಎತ್ತುತ್ತಿರುವದು ಸ್ವಾಗತಾರ್ಹ . ಒಬ್ಬ ಮಹಿಳೆಗೆ ತನ್ನ ಮೇಲಾದ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ಸಹಿಸಿಕೊಳ್ಳುವದು‌ ಕಷ್ಟಕರ ಸಂಗತಿ . ಸತ್ಯ ಯಾವಾಗ ಹೇಳಿದರೂ ಅದು ಸತ್ಯವೇ ಆಗಿರುತ್ತದೆ . ಆರೋಪಿಗಳೆಲ್ಲರಿಗೂ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆ ಆಗದಿದ್ದರೂ , ಕೆಲವರಿಗಾದರೂ ಶಿಕ್ಷೆಯಾಗಲಿ ಅನ್ನೋದು ನಮ್ಮ ಆಶಯ . ಇದರಿಂದಾಗಿ ಮುಂದಿನ ದಿನಗಳಲ್ಲಿ ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ಮಾಡುವವರು ವಿಚಾರ ಮಾಡುವಂತಾಗುತ್ತದೆ . ಇದೆಲ್ಲವೂ ಮೀಡಿಯಾಗಳಿಂದ ಸೆನ್ಸೇಷನಲ್ ಆಗುತ್ತಿವೆ ಎಂದು ನಟಿ ಶೃತಿ ಹರಿಹರನ್ ಹೇಳಿದರು . ಲೈಂಗಿಕ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯದಲ್ಲಿ ಗಂಡು ಮತ್ತು ಹೆಣ್ಣಿನ ಪ್ರಶ್ನೆ ಬರಲ್ಲ . ಅಧಿಕಾರ ಬಲ ಹಾಗೂ ಹಣಬಲದಿಂದ ಇಂತ ಕೃತ್ಯ ನಡೆಯುತ್ತಿವೆ . ಇದನ್ನು ತಡೆಯುವ ನಿಟ್ಟಿನಲ್ಲಿ ಚಲಚಿತ್ರ ವಾಣಿಜ್ಯ ಮಂಡಳಿಗಳೂ ಕೂಡಾ ಕಾಳಜಿವಹಿಸುತ್ತಿವೆ . ಅಭಿಯಾನದಲ್ಲಿ ಕವಿತಾ ಲಂಕೇಶ್​ ಹಾಗೂ ನಾನು ಸೇರಿದಂತೆ ಹಲವರು ಭಾಗಿಯಾಗಿ ಧ್ವನಿ ಎತ್ತಲಿದ್ದೇವೆ ಎಂದರು .

text:
in a move that came as a complete shocker and also an eye-opener to the film fraternity, superstar akshay kumar has decided to cancel the shooting of his upcoming film "housefull 4"

other day three different women have accused director-producer sajid khan of sexual harassment, while he's preparing from the shooting of housefull 4 that will resume today. and then we have actor nana patekar playing a crucial role in this film and he is also facing sexual harassment case from heroine tanushree dutta. 
informing about the cancellation of the shoot, akshay said, "i've just landed back in the country last night and reading all the news has been very disturbing. i've requested the producers of housefull 4 to cancel the shoot until further investigation.". adding more about #metoo movement, he said, "this is something that requires stringent action. i will not work with any proven offenders and all those who have been subjugated to harassment should be heard and given the justice they deserve". reacting on the same, director-producer sajid khan tweeted, "in the wake of the allegations against me & the pressure being put on my family, my producer n the stars of my film houseful4, i must take the moral responsibility of stepping down from my directorial post, till the time i can allay the allegations and prove the truth.. i request my friends in the media to kindly not pass judgment till the truth is out". housefull 4 has popular telugu heroines like kriti sanon, kriti kharbanda and pooja hegde in the leads alongside akshay kumar and ritesh deshmukh. 
#akshaykumar #sajidkhan .

text:
many of you have been expressing how much #yourstorymedicine is bringing up emotionally/spiritually/physically. these past two weeks have been especially difficult for folks who are survivors, but now more than ever is the time for us to remind each other of our worth. i recently shared #survivorloveletter, a campaign started by my friend @taniikeda three years ago - and since then it has taken a life of its own. a beautiful mural honoring this movement was just completed in new york, and tani will now be road tripping cross country back to los angeles while sharing more letters in public spaces to reach and inspire more survivors.

are you interested in being a part of this movement? if so, share 1-3 lines (short!) in the comments below.  your words will be converted into an art installation rippled across the us. 🎨  @survivor.love.letter 
think of how many people are afraid to speak up and share their story right now, but it doesn’t mean their experiences aren’t valid. we will not be silenced. 💕 #ibelieveyou #metoo ✊🏾 ⬇️

text:
i love being a woman's woman. i really do. i've been holding this thought carefully, balancing it on the planes of my palm for fear it would break. but it strengthens with every exchange like the one i had with @bossladycreates yesterday, and with others in this fight.
.
.
the destructive trope of the cool girl, first eviscerated for me in @gillianflynnofficial's gone girl, has been laid to rest. the era of the woman's woman is in full force.
.
.
i feel it more strongly every time i discover someone doing similar work. with a like, a follow, an encouraging word, you tell me there's room for me. and my purest instinct is to pay it forward. .
.
come on over. sit with me. talk with me. the table is never full. we create space for each other when we move closer together. .
#thewordforthis #metoo #believesurvivors #whyididntreport #womenempowerment #womensupportingwomen #empoweringwomen #thiswomanswork

(art by @yukoart 🙏🌟) this gorgeous artwork comes on the international day of the girl. what i love most about my life are the people in it, the majority of whom are women. my sisters, my best friends, my mother & mother-in-law & grandmothers & obaachan... this day is to celebrate women and girls. 👏🌟 i recognize all that women endure, especially women of color, around the world. i commend the mothers risking everything to immigrate, the girls defecting in north korea, girls fighting for education, girls in refugee camps, every woman sharing or thinking #metoo. women’s successes and contributions to society cannot be diminished, no matter how patriarchal history tried to do so. women, womyn, girls of every color, orientation, ethnicity, religion: you are valued. anyone reading this, we are who our ancestors prayed for. we have the power to support our sisters in our communities and around the world. let’s make the choice to be inclusive of all women. let’s make this happen. please vote. and please, donate. @dayofthegirlsummit @dayofthegirl @zanaafricafoundation @malala @obamafoundation .
.
.

text:
pagirios yra zajebimba

vienžo', tęsiu savo istorijų seriją instagrame apie visokius šūdinus nutikimus.

kartais būna iš vakaro padauginu velnio lašų, kas šiaip nėra blogai, blogai yra tas, jog iš ryto man būna žiauriai negera. atsikeliu lyg su švininiu tvarsčiu ant galvos, skauda šonus, plaučius, rankas, sielą, ima nervas, paranoja kilnoja stogą ir taip visą dieną sergi realiu aids.

ir nieko negali dėl to daryt. tu tik prakairuoji ir dejuoji. o ką, ką, bet aš skųstis ir dejuot, tai mėgstu labiau negu valgyt. neduok pavalgyt, o duok padejuot.

ir vat tokiais sunkiais momentais kaip tyčia pasitaiko ir gerai besijaučiant nepakeliami darbai. labai ankstyvoje jaunystėje tėvai versdavo iš lovos, po gero baliaus sterviake, ir važiuodavom kaiman kokios nors chujnios daryt. o nuotraukos darymo momentu supratau, jog teks važiuot vilniaus viešuoju transportu, kas yra vienas iš devynių pragaro ratų.

daug netrinsiu: važiavau autubiku, o priešais mane sėdėjo kažkokia porelė. ausinėse pliekė "šiaurės miestelis" podcastas/spektaklis, tai nelabai kreipiau dėmesį į tai, jog važiuojant sudejavau kokius 347 kartus.

o kadangi buvau su lietpalčiu ir įsikišęs rankas į kišenes, išmuštas priešmirtinio prakaito, bei visas dejuojantis agonijoje, kažkuriuo momentu suvokiau, jog iš šono atrodau taip lyg paslapčia vaškuočiau savo lenkišką kielbasą.

atlikęs tos dienos misijas (reikėjo aplankyt big smoke), atsisėdau prie mažvydo bibliotekos esančiame parkelyje, bei pasidžiaugiau rudeniu ir monsteriu. savęs nebeišėjo apgaudinėti daugiau, tad teko pripažinti, jog dėl to kas šiandien įvyko, greičiausiai niekada gyvenime negalėsiu užimti jokio politinio posto.

#nekliuda2034 #tbt #pachmiel #reklam #metoo #aistukė

text:
i am incredibly proud to be a woman. however, i do realize the unfortunate truth that because of my gender, i and other women, are subject to countless degrading remarks from not only men, but other women as well. now, just because i know this, it doesn’t mean i accept it. i do not tolerate victim blaming/slut-shaming/sexism in any way, shape, or form. because it is wrong and incredibly disrespectful. another thing that comes along with being a woman is the fear of sexual assault and harassment. from a young age i was taught to go in “packs” just to use the restroom & to cover my open cup at parties. i am not allowed to get into a taxi/uber alone ever, and i was also taught that i had to dress modestly in order to prevent any “unwanted advances”. so, are women really equal to their male counterparts? well, in some things yes, but in the majority of other things.... no. of course it’s good to teach our girls to protect themselves, but there needs to be a different approach to how we teach them about these issues. when we instill the idea that what they wear = the attention they attract, we are also instilling the idea that if their skirts were too short, they were “asking for it.” this is absolutely disgusting. i will no longer accept this from anyone. if you have a daughter, teach her to protect herself but also teach her the importance of standing with her fellow women in the fight against sexual assault and domestic violence. teach her to embrace her body and not feel ashamed of how she dresses. lastly, we should be standing with women not because of the role they play in our lives, but because we are your fellow human beings. ✨✨✨
men: respect women. understand that no means no. call out your male counterparts who don’t understand the value of respecting women & their bodies. 
ladies: stick up for each other. don’t slut shame. look out for each other and respect each other. [ #beautifulworld #quotes #pasttpresenttfuturee #woman #shemustcount #timesup #metoo #cosmos #healthesoul #losangeles ]
name: 𝙈𝙚𝙡𝙞𝙣𝙖 𝙁𝙖𝙧𝙖𝙝𝙢𝙖𝙣𝙙 🌹 || ＵＳ. ＮＡＶＹ

i am incredibly proud to be a woman. however, i do realize the unfounate truth that because of my gender, i and other women, are subject to countless degrading remarks from not only men, but other women as well. now, just because i know this, it doesn’t mean i accept it. i do not tolerate victim blaming/slut-shaming/sexism in any way, shape, or form. because it is wrong and incredibly disrespectful. another thing that comes along with being a woman is the fear of sexual assault and harassment. from a young age i was taught to go in “packs” just to use the restroom & to cover my open cup at paies. i am not allowed to get into a taxi/uber alone ever, and i was also taught that i had to dress modestly in order to prevent any “unwanted advances”. so, are women really equal to their male counterpas? well, in some things yes, but in the majority of other things.... no. of course it’s good to teach our girls to protect themselves, but there needs to be a different approach to how we teach them about these issues. when we instill the idea that what they wear = the attention they attract, we are also instilling the idea that if their skis were too sho, they were “asking for it.” this is absolutely disgusting. i will no longer accept this from anyone. if you have a daughter, teach her to protect herself but also teach her the impoance of standing with her fellow women in the fight against sexual assault and domestic violence. teach her to embrace her body and not feel ashamed of how she dresses. lastly, we should be standing with women not because of the role they play in our lives, but because we are your fellow human beings. ✨✨✨
men: respect women. understand that no means no. call out your male counterpas who don’t understand the value of respecting women & their bodies.

what does it mean to stand in your truth?⠀⠀
⠀⠀
⠀⠀
it is easy, when things feel hard or insurmountable, to hide behind our stories. ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
we end up presenting only a part of ourselves to the world, the part that we think the world wants to hear or the one that "makes sense".⠀⠀
⠀⠀
⠀⠀
but is that really enough?⠀⠀
⠀⠀
in today's solo episode, betsy is sitting down to share her story—her true story—not the story she's hidden behind for the last 20 years.⠀⠀
⠀⠀
it's the story that has shaped who she is, how she shows up in the world and illustrates that when you stand in your truth, you have the power to rewrite old stories and transform your life.⠀⠀
⠀⠀

text:
yesterday was international day of the girl! i was going to post this yesterday but instead decided today because every day should be international day of the girl, and the boy! as cliché as it sounds, they really are the future
——
.
earlier this week i posted some stories about me cleaning everything out of my boys room bc they were being rude, disrespectful and messy and i wanted to teach them a lesson. i’ll be honest, it must have hit a nerve with some people. i did get some negative comments  and that’s ok. we are all entitled  to our own opinions. but the more i thought about it, the more i realized, i have more to say about raising boys!
——
.  this little women, my little side kick, my future crazy plant lady, the one with attitude in the morning and cuddly feelings at night, a true daddy’s girl who can hold her own with her brothers - she is the reason i try to hard to raise my boys right. by right i mean to respect, understand, appreciate, and have compassion for everyone (especially women). i want them to work hard, learn how to do housework, be amazing engaged fathers, be kind, cook, have meaningful relationships, be ok with emotions,  and most of all be happy loving men and future husbands!  i owe that to them!
——
.

my baby girl deserve to be around that. your baby girl deserves that. i want her to know that she deserve that.  i also want her to know that she is expected to do the same.  she, as a girl, soon to be women,  must understand that what she expects from men, must also be expected of her. we are all in this together and must teach our children to work together, to be a team, to understand and respect each other.
——-
.

we may mess up along the way but, being mindfully aware and at least trying to raise better people is moving in the right direction. change starts with the next generation.  and if that means teaching punk attitude boys a lesson by cleaning every treasured toy out their rooms, then so be it!  cheers to all the moms and future moms - mommin is hard! ❤️💪🏼#respectstartsathome #ihaveavoice
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#offmysoapbox #raisingkids #happyfriday #beingamomishard #futuregeneration #inspiration #mommin #mommingainteasy

text: how many times have you been told to “let it go”? instead of viewing anger as something to suppress, rebecca traister delves into the revolutionary power of rage, specifically women’s rage, in her brand new book “good and mad”. long before the women’s march began or the #metoo movement dominated conversation, women have led social and political change by channeling injustices that made them angry. the book is inspiring, enraging, and it teaches a side of history that has often been misunderstood, marginalized, and ignored. it will make you want to own your anger and channel it into a constructive way to make change. grab a copy and rage through the weekend. #feministfriday #bookclub #goodandmad #rebeccatraister 📷📝: @bartielouscott

text:
#featurefriday nadia murad & dr. denis mukwege (📸: ap photos/christian lutz, 2016) 
_______
background: for the next couple months, we'll be featuring global, national, and local influencers who are taking action against sexual harassment. 
_______
nadia murad: 24-year-old nadia murad was among thousands of yazidi women who were abducted and enslaved by the self-proclaimed islamic state (isis). after 3 months in captivity, where she was subjected to rape and other sexual violences, she managed to flee. since then, she's become a global spokeswomen on sexual-violence issues. she has spoken on numerous occasions about her experience, bringing light to sexual assaults in global conflicts. this past friday, she was awarded, along with dr. mukwege, the nobel peace prize for her work against sexual violence. 
_______
dr. denis mukwege: mukwege, 63, is a congolese gynecologist and medical director of panzi hospital in bukavu, south kivu (a province in the eastern congo), an area "which has been blightened by more than 2 decades of conflict" (bloomberg). mukwege founded panzi in 1999. since its opening, the hospital has offered obstetric care and treatment for severe gynecological problems (bloomberg). throughout his practice, mukwege has treated victims of gang rape and other sexual violences. he was awarded the nobel peace prize along with nadia murad this past friday for his work.
(photo credit: ap photos/christian lutz, 2016) 
_______
#onceandforall #timesup #nothere #metoo

text:
cuando #murphybrown salió por primera vez a antena en #1989 yo tenía 10 años y  la #serie la ponían a las tantas en la dos, en una televisión española que sólo tenía cinco canales. y confieso que desde el primer momento pensé que de mayor quería ser #murphy ( una mujer independiente, que decía lo que pensaba en todo momento y era un referente femenino). 30 años después hacen un #reboot de la serie y son de esas series que es imposible volver hacerla con nuevos actores porque el alma de murphy brown se llama #candicebergen.  un estilo a #thexfiles que sin #gilliananderson y #davidduchovny sería inimaginable.

el primer episodio ha sido destornillante, la escena del primer #tweet de murphy y el cameo de #hillaryclinton nivelazo. y la cita con #donaldtrump me parto.

no tendrá buen #share pero me importa un bledo, yo estoy más feliz que una perdiz. gracias #usa por no tener nuevas ideas y traer lo mejor de #90s .

#usa #cbs #washingtondc #actress #comedy #ny #awards #icon #style #beauty #journalist  #feminist #arethafranklin #metoo #women #hollywood

text:
pink villa:“sanaya irani lauds akshay for canceling shoot of housefull 4 post sajid khan's sexual harassment allegations

me too movement is gaining momentum in india and many celebs from bollywood and tv worlds are being called out as they allegedly sexually harassed and assaulted women. nana patekar, vivek agnihotri, alok nath, vikas bahl, rajat kapoor, zulfi syed, and kailash kher among others are in the list and it seems the list is never-ending as new names are adding up every other day. now reportedly famous filmmaker sajid khan is also accused of sexual harassment and misconduct. akshay kumar gave out a tweet and revealed that he won't continue the shoot of housefull 4 amid the allegations on sajid khan who is the helmer of the movie

many celebs have commented on the ongoing metoo movement and sanaya irani, the famous tv star has also commented on the same. she took to the instagram story to share the story of sajid khan and wrote how this needs to happen and she also mentioned hashtags timesup and metoo” #metoo #timesup
.
.
.
موقع بينك فيلا:”سنايا ايراني تمدح اكشاي كومار لالغاءه تصوير house full 4 بعد تعدي المخرج ساجيد خان على واحدة من طاقم العمل

حركة me too (الحركة المساندة للبنت الي تم التعدي عليها) حازت على اهتمام كبير في الهند، و الكثير من النجوم في بوليود و التلفزيون دعموا هذه الحركة بما انها تدافع عن انتهاك حقوق المرأة. نانا باتيكار، فيفيك، الوك، فيكاس، راجات، زولفي، كايلاش و اسماء اخرى كثيرة تضاف للقائمة يوميا و التي يبدو انها لن تنتهي (الاسماء منهم ضحايا اعتداء و الي قاموا بالتعدي). و الان المخرج و المنتج المعروف ساجيد خان ايضا تم اتهامه بالتعدي و محاولة الاغتصاب، اكشاي كومار نشر تغريدة قال فيها انه لن يكمل تصوير house full 4 بعد ما فعله مخرج العمل ساجيد خان.

العديد من المشاهير علقوا على حركة me too القائمة و منهم سنايا ايراني، ممثلة التلفزيون المشهورة ايضاً علقت عليها، نشرتها عبر الانستغرام ستوري الخاص بها و قالت ان هذا حقاً يجب ان يحدث و وضعت هاشتاجات "لقد انتهى الوقت" و "me too".“
بلد متخلفة حسبي الله و نعم الوكيل في كل واحد شغال في الحكومة الحقيرة دي و مبيراعيش ضميرة كل يوم قضية زفت زي دي و الحكومة واقفة تبتسم! ربنا يتوب على سنايا من ام البلد دي خسارة فيهم اصلا 😒 فخورة بيها ❤

text:
lady dysp breaks silence, accuses former dir vigilance of ‘sexual harassment’
jammu: former director, vigilance and retired ips officer, alok pur is another name floating on the internet since the recent eruption of the #metoo movement in india.
deputy superintendent of police (dysp) shashi thakur has taken to twitter—complaining against alleged “sexual harassment” by then director vigilance. 1984 ips batch officer, puri retired as adgp (crime) in jammu and kashmir.
“i raised voice against land mafia in my state (j&k) but had to face sexual harassment in the hands of then director vigilance alok puri. despite complaints against him that filed no one took action against him,” dysp thakur wrote on twitter triggering a debate about safety of women in workspace.
“waiting for justice,” she wrote at the end, while hoping for justice under governor satyal paul malik’s rule in jammu and kashmir.
#metoo campaign has gained strength in society especially after women came forward to openly speak up against their harassers, while seeking justice.
dysp thakur, told rising kashmir that she is being harassed from last seven years and justice has yet not delivered. “i made a complaint but then director vigilance alok puri remained unpunished despite complaint at the chief vigilance commission’s office. they too, wrote to alok puri asking him to look into the issue. the issue was dumped, later,” she alleged.
the aggrieved lady officer said that she raised voice against the encroachment on state land in sunjwan. the encroachment was facilitated by the revenue department and local police. even as vigilance filed a report recommending fir in the case after three years of investigation, then director vigilance did not file the fir.”
dysp said “since i was pursuing the case, i went to meet then director vigilance alok puri and requested him to file fir as recommended by the vigilance. but he was reluctant.”
instead of doing his job, she claimed “alok puri directly asked me for sexual favour. but, i declined and came out of his office.”
“if you (thakur) want fir in the case, then you have to compromise with me,” the dysp thakur quoted alok puri as saying. she said the file was on his

text:
friday's prompt is social/current affairs
.
what gets taken away at the moment a line is crossed? in my case the first time an incident of molestation happened i was too young to comprehend, let alone resist. for many years i locked it away in my mind, impervious to its effects. the second time it happened i was old enough to know what it was, but the laws of workplace harassment were not on my side, and i had to quit my job to go on dole in paris as an immigrant. the third time the line was crossed, it was by somebody i considered a close friend, and in trying to fathom how somebody who claimed to care for me could not understand the word "no", my mind literally went into overdrive and shattered into pieces.
.
the past few days with their outpouring of stories has had me by turns enraged, sad and anxious. i'm disheartened to see what a long way we still have to go and how much anger has built up on one side. now that the dams have broken we are going to have to navigate some very messy waters before arriving at something like light.
.
let's face it: no matter how much we try to arrive at a perfect communication of consent, it's never that easy in real life. society has done much to create a whole host of non-verbal gestures that are supposed to mean yes when the lady is actually saying no: smiling, drinking, wearing short or revealing clothes, expressing platonic interest, being generous and kind, the list goes on. in my case, instead of asking the perpetrator why he did such a thing to me, i turned on myself and asked myself why i had all these qualities. what gets taken away in the moment is more than just trust, but your very idea of your self, which comes undone as you begin to question everything.
.
becoming whole again can take years but the first step towards solace is knowing that at the moment the line was being crossed, you could do only one thing: say no. and i did. every time.
.
this is a picture taken in rome of a sculpture called the abduction of persephone, now more aptly called the rape of persephone
. 
#metoo #metoomovement #healing #consent

‼️‼️ please watch 👀 this video !! 🛑 lynette medley tyra ceo/founder of @no_moresecrets469  is doing what nobody wants to do ! have these crucial conversations in our community! 👋🏽 crucial conversations are vital !! 🤔 the concepts of consent and bodily autonomy are ambiguous to our youth so 😩 please stop 🛑 telling her that youth/teens in your home, community, schools, churches etc . already know this and don’t need these classes.. because they don’t ⚠️😕! 😔 due to their inability to completely comprehend the power they possess over their bodies at all times they make decisions based off of distorted .. perceptions and perspectives 👊🏽. this is due to the stigmas, silence and secrecy associated with sexuality awareness !! so when you wonder why women and men 😔😔😔 wait up to 10 years to finally come forward about sexual assault, rape or molestation !! it’s because most didn’t even realize that they had actually been violated at that time , many don’t realize until years later when they hear 👂🏽 and gain a clear understanding of appropriate sexual encounters and boundaries. !! awareness plus education and action are key ! 
please schedule nomore secrets mbs  a realistic approach to sexual health to speak with your youth asap!
we save lives by changing minds 😍!
nomoresecretsmbs.org

text:
the past few weeks have been difficult for all of us.
but also, we're witnessing a movement. an ongoing, much needed one. 
imagine that. women having found a way around the justice system that failed us, a campaign that was unplanned, not choreographed and unfolded organically, courageously.
and the tables that are turning now!
we do wish that #metooindia finds a place in the deepest corners of the country taking shape from their own forms of oppression, patriarchy, abuse and inequality. 
but for now
this is a collective victory, and it stands for all of us, even those who could not speak up and cannot, more power to you! .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
while giving her speech at the frankfurt book fair, adichie at the opening of the world's biggest publishing event said, "all over the world today women are speaking up. their stories are still not really heard"

women are still invisible. women's experiences are still invisible.

a year after the #metoo movement went viral and ignited a global discussion about sexual harassment, adichie said there was much work left to be done.

it is time for us to pay more than lip service to the fact that women's stories are for everyone.

we know from studies that women read books by men and women. but men read books by men. it is time for men to read women.

in a thinly veiled reference to us judge brett kavanaugh's controversial confirmation to the supreme court despite accusations of sexual misconduct, adichie slammed the tendency not to believe victims of such assaults.

she said: "we seem to live in a world where many people believe large numbers of women can simply wake up one day and make up stories about having been assaulted.

i know many women who want to be famous. i don't know one single woman who wants to be famous for having been assaulted.
.
.
.
#allcelebritygist
#chimamandangoziadichie
#celebritynews

text:
the first "experience" i remember having was so young that i honestly blocked so much but the earliest one i remember was when i was around 8 years old, i remember having my first "encounter with a sexual context" that shouldn't have happened. it wasn't until years later that i even realized what had actually happened. for so many the "victims" are completely unaware of what's going on until it is too late. i like so many thought that it was normal passed it on. now as an adult with children of my own i cringe at the thought of what was going on with me then and possibly sooner and i pray they dont experience anything close and if they ever do they know they can always trust me and know i'll always be there to hear anything they say, no judgments ever! i've been lucky to have married a man that is not only beyond respectful and understanding with me but one that also teaches and will continue to teach our daughters to always feel comfortable to speak up and say no! it's always ok to say no....
.
.
when was the first time or last time you should have said no, but had no idea? or were too afraid? or just plane had that choice taken from you? if the answer to that is anything other then never then it too many times and it should never have happened...
.
.
#metoo #hertoo #whyididntreportit

text: welcome to my blog! this is something that i’ve wanted to start for a long time and never quite had the courage to do, mostly for fear of social backlash/legal charges. but i’ve been lucky enough to have gone through something which recently taught me that, however scary something seems, the truth really does set you free ✨ and through this blog, i want to share my truth with you all by shedding light on what it really means to be a feminist and a woman in qatar. i want to show people the truth i see in my beliefs and through that, i hope to create something here that is intersectional, inspirational, and introspective for myself and others 🌻

text: i wrote y’all another poem. brilliant artist that i am. 🙇🏽‍♀️✨🙌🏽 positive affirmations are awesome, self care tips are super, but what survivors and women really need to thrive are rights. legal protections. reliable federal resources. bodily autonomy. health care. and we secure these by voting. voting is a positive affirmation. voting is self care. voting is survival. and survival is what we do. i know a lot of us voted in 2016 and were dealt a blow that seemed insurmountable. but we can’t give up. we can’t shut up. because that’s how they win. when we all vote, we can change the world. when we all vote, we all do better. vote, y’all. 🙏🏽 🇺🇸✔️ #vote #whenweallvote #survivor #believesurvivors #selfcare #healing #survivorselfcare #metoo

text:
समाजवादी विचारक और नेता राम मनोहर लोहिया की बरसी है 12 अक्टूबर को. इस मौके पर पढ़िए औरतों के नाम उनकी एक सलाह. भारत में #metoo कैंपेन चल रहा है इन दिनों. ऐसे में मर्दों और औरतों, और बाकी सारे जेंडर्स को भी लोहिया की कही ये बात पढ़नी चाहिए.

आज के हिंदुस्तान में एक मर्द और एक औरत शादी करके जो सात-आठ बच्चे पैदा करते हैं उनके बनिस्बत मैं उनको पसंद करूंगा जो बिना शादी किए हुए एक भी नहीं या एक ही पैदा करते हैं. या, लड़की यानी उसके मां-बाप दहेज देकर, जिसे समाज कहेगा अच्छी-खासी शादी, उसको मैं ज्यादा खराब समझूंगा बनिस्बत एक ऐसी लड़की के जो कि दहेज दिए बिना दुनिया में आत्म-सम्मान के साथ चलती है और फिर ऐसे कुछ प्रसंग हो जाते हैं कि समाज कहे कि यह कहां की छिनाल आई. मर्द छिनालों की तो हिंदुस्तान में निंदा नहीं होती लेकिन औरत छिनालों की निंदा हो जाती है.
name: हिन्द प्रभात

text:
#hurricaneallie and i have been spending a lot more time together. i wouldn't change a thing in the world. our daddy-daughter time really means a lot to me since i've finally found a way to bond with allie. the way she looks at me just melts my heart and all i can see is something perfect.

with all the talk going around about harassment and the whole #metoo movement, i started wondering what kind of world my daughter will grow up in. the idea of her being in a situation where she's powerless makes me worry. i've probably played my part by encouraging "boys will be boys" mentality. more importantly, it's in my control to change that behaviour.

i owe it to her to start being a good role model to other guys and show the world that chivalry is still alive. i will remember to be kind, to respect everyone, to listen, to encourage independence and equality.

#chivalryisnotdead #iwill #daddyenabler #daddydaughtertime #daddiesgirl #beproactive #startswithme

text:
the story goes like this
i:

i don’t know why i took photos the morning after i was assaulted. i woke up at 6am, about 3-4 hours after it happened, and immediately started capturing images of my bedroom and my body through tears swelling up in my eyes. i’m surprised any are in focus.

when #drchristineblaseyford raised her right hand in the senate judiciary committee and swore to tell the truth, her testimony became an invitation for victims to speak up—no matter how long ago the assault, how violent the attack, how powerful the accused or how official the report.

as the #metoomovement gained headlines last year, i remember feeling lucky that i was 29 years old and had not been sexually assaulted. a month later that changed. almost a year later, i am ready to share the images i took the morning after and the days directly following.

thank you for being here.
•
•
•
•
•
since may 2017, @britt.teas has been working with @_michelleyee as part of @sofiasofiato’s inaugural mentorship program. she will be sharing a series of images and writing about sexual assault titled “the story goes like this" as part of her mentorship with michelle. britt received her mfa in creative nonfiction writing from @ukchalifax and has been documenting her life by way of pen and 35mm photography for over a decade. #ibelievechristineblaseyford #believesurvivors #thestorygoeslikethis #metoo #metoomvmt #drfordloveletter #girlgaze

text:
friday, and i'm reading papers
that i got this morning
talking about stuff- #metoo
and all that, it's taxing
reading the words of a writer
who wrote as if writing
should only be done with verbose.
i hate this piece;
the juxtaposition of words rearranged,
realigned with convoluted descriptions
of lacerations of the psyche
which culminates to the utter abandon
of form, whilst resonating with pompous
overtones as if the scribe who
conveyed the script is clearly in contempt
at the populace who do not
have a clear apprehension of the vernacular
he or she uses to paint pictures with.

i detest these people.
they are clearly flawed. 
not in the syntaxes 
of their linguistic obsession,
but in their desire to appear
more formal and polite.
their flaw is remarkable,
yet they would make you think
they are different.
fuck these people. fuck their form.
fuck their genteel ways.
and fuck their pseudointellectuality.

text:
four retired judges to conduct public hearings of #metoo cases, says union minister maneka gandhi
*
*

new delhi: the government will form a committee of four retired judges to conduct public hearings on the #metoo movement's allegations of sexual harassment, said union minister maneka gandhi on friday.
.
the committee will look into all issues emanating from #metoo movement, said gandhi, 
the #metoo movement has gathered pace over the last fortnight with scores of women coming forward with personal accounts of sexual harassment by colleagues and bosses.
.
several filmmakers and actors, politicians and journalists have been named in a wave of sexual misconduct allegations, spurred on by actor tanushree dutta's claims that she was harassed by her colleague nana patekar on the sets of a 2008 movie.

text:
i have an extra smile with all the #metoo campaigns in our country.
kudos to all the girls who have the courage to call a spade a spade, albeit a bit late but it’s never too late.
while the wave is quite a tumultuous affair for the film fraternity - harassment is rampant in every sector. right from education to politics to medicine to it. even the home is not safe.
i urge women to push away the shackles of being a victim  or feel ashamed - we have the power to pull down the criminals and stop many from being victimised.
.
it’s a shout-out to all the sanskari men who felt, men must grope, must rape, must abuse, must torture females. what gives you this power? is it because they are born with a tissue dangling between their two legs?
it’s a shout-out to the owners of that vulnerable tissue - live and let live - else get ready to be hurt where it really hurts.
.
it’s a shout-out to those men who have not grown up in their mind - beware, it won’t take long for the oppressed victims much time to open up and show you what it takes to be a victim.
.
there is a part of he in every she!
let not the shhhhh in women make you think she is weak.
forget not, if she can bear pain - she can inflict pain too.
let there be peace.
let there be respect.
.
my entry to festive mood in my off white  noil saree from  @nextiles  i had to have a bit of devi on me and there goes the hand painted and hand made necklace.
.
#sareelove #sareenme #sareesisterhood #whitenred #weavesofindia

text:
yong-soo lee touches my women’s column of strength, the san francisco “#comfortwomen” memorial statue. 
lee, 89, who was kidnapped from her home in korea at the age of 15 and forced to work in a taiwan “comfort station” that served japanese soldiers, fought back tears as she said that the experience of seeing the monument was “too much to talk about” and that she is “still suffering from the pain and torture.”

text: this is mental health awareness week!  i was always raised to search for the answers to happiness outside of myself.  society teaches us this from a young age, commercials, music, all of social media points to happiness is something we have to acquire.  the wait is over my friends!  the great news is that we were born to actually be our own true beloved and until we learn this completely, we go from relationship to relationship, one addiction to another looking for love.  once we learn that our true beloved is within and learn to fall in love with who we are, then we begin to attract others that are not so needy.  this results in relationships where we can play and have fun together!  being sober was a way to stop the madness inside and the chaos i kept my life in long enough to begin this courageous journey.  yes i am a recovering alcoholic and always will be, and yes whatever the doctors say to the insurance companies to help me with any mid firings i may have in my brain are needed. i learned that the diagnoses are none of my business and do not define me today.  i just show up and do not abuse any meds, take them exactly as prescribed and my life is so simple instead of me playing doctor.  today i am humble enough to stay on my meds for my sake and my family’s sake.  i know what goes on in my head when i don’t take them and it is not acceptable to me.  if you have meds, take them, yet remember that they are to help you, not hurt you.  they do not define you. mental illness is real, yet it need not define you.  i have worked hard to be healthy in sobriety and i will not allow anyone to limit me or label me.  #soberwomen #aa #onedayatatime #attitudeofgratitude #billw #mentalhealthawareness #sobrietyrocks #sobrietyforwomen #mentalhealth #metoo #timesup #metooneveryou #believeher #sexualtrauma #traumahealing #recoveryispossible #theshamelesswarrior

text_retweet:
i have been so busy with work, life, and dealing with a similar situation that i am barely getting caught up on what’s been going on with our country. the timing in this is mind blowing, but that’s for another day. any person (& not just women) who have experienced something like this just knows she was telling the truth. you can see, feel and hear it from her. and if that isn’t enough, you can see, feel and hear the lies from him. you can catch the tiny itty bitty smirks that accidentally slipped out for half a second on his face. i can go on and on.. but we all know. .
.
usually for a business/professional page, it would be best to avoid politics and/or something like this. but it’s 2018, i am a woman, a warrior, and a minority.. i can do anything i want. so if discussing an uncomfortable topic and exposing reality so that survivors & warriors no longer are hushed and predators & monsters can feel uncomfortable, unsafe, & exposed - then i’m all for it. times are changing, the fight is nonstop. our current leadership is proof of how they will try to remain in power and hush us.. but the future when this will no longer be tolerated, excused, or paid off is getting closer and closer. we just have to keep fighting, more will continue to standup & make a difference.

the full love letter will touch you so deeply. i encourage all to read it and sign it. i’ll keep the link in my bio temporarily so you can easily access it. #drfordloveletter #metoo .
.
.
@get_repost
・・・
dr. blasey ford’s testimony before the senate judiciary committee in september was one of the most courageous acts we have ever witnessed. despite the harassment, maligning, and ridicule she has had to endure, she remains a hero for so many survivors, allies, and supporters around the world.

this letter is our love offering to her so that she has a constant reminder that there is enormous support for her and other survivors like her. we heard her. we saw her. and we believed her.

see the full letter to dr. blasey ford and add your signature via the link in our bio.

written by tarana burke, amanda de cadenet, glennon doyle, tracee ellis ross, & america ferrera. #drfordloveletter

text: #powerofcourage #powerofcompassion when pow’s foundeess #drpriyavirmani gave a talk in india last year on the #metoo movement that was taking shape in the west, many women came to her and spoke about their stories of violence, assault and abuse at the hands of men, most of them men in their lives - relatives, husbands, boyfriends and bosses. and of children being violated - mostly within the space of the family. she hoped they would find the courage to speak out, that metoo would reach india and give the perpetrating men no space to hide. today it has reached india, we all at #paintourworld applaud every woman responsible for being the light, so such men and their behaviour have no dark spaces to hide. priya’s metoo talk from november 2017 has just been uploaded on youtube https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=d6xcc8onseo

text:
silent protest again all the difficulties we face as women, people with different genders, sexualities, races and people who face violence. we are all worth something and none of us deserve the slurs, bigotry, hatred, and abuse that we are subjected to purely based on something we did not want or choose to be but something that makes us our intrinsic self. each piece of you makes up your identity as a whole and if some piece of that identity is marginalised and torn away from you then it makes you feel like less of a person but you need to remember that you have grown stronger bolder and way more beautiful and they can never ever take away from you that identity!
